Worth the hype? 💧

You’ve probably seen electrolyte drinks and powders trending all over social media this month, with promises of ‘better hydration’. But what most people don’t realise is that the majority of the products being sold to you are just expensive mixes of sugar, sweeteners and salt with clever marketing – exactly the kind of added ingredients that many of us are trying to reduce.

Check the video for a typical electrolyte drink recipe - high sugar, high salt 👆

That’s not to say they don’t have a role. If you have diarrhoea or vomiting, a high stoma output, are sweating excessively in a hot climate, or are exercising at an intense level for more than an hour (dripping in sweat the whole time), then sure. Electrolyte drinks can be a handy tool to restore and maintain body salts, which helps to maximise fluid absorption from your gut, amongst many other functions. But for the average person looking to stay hydrated day-to-day? There’s no magic here. Regular water will do just fine.

Takehome...
💧 If you want to know if you’re hydrated enough, check your urine. If it’s dark and strong smelling, it’s a sign that you need to drink more water. You should aim to get to a pale colour that’s odourless (unless you’ve eaten asparagus, that is). 
💧 Instead of reaching for an electrolyte drink to support hydration, try adding some of your favourite fruits and veggies to your water bottle - like cucumber, berries, mint or basil - to encourage you to sip on it more frequently throughout the day.

It’s not as simple as calories in vs calories out...❌ 
*trigger warning for those living with or recovering from an ED*

Did you know your body burns calories by eating and digesting food? It’s known as the thermogenic effect of food. But here’s the key, the type of food you eat matters. 

Whole foods like fruits, nuts, and wholegrains make your body work harder, burning more energy in the process. But when it comes to ultra-processed foods (UPFs), it’s a different story. Machines have done most of the work for you, so your body burns fewer calories digesting them, as much as 50% less compared to whole foods. 

This is just one of many examples of why calorie fixation is flawed, not to meantion how it ignores the full picture of health. It also explains why the research shows that any “results” you might see are often short lived. 

If your New Year goal is reaching your happy weight (not forgetting your wider health goals), here are 3 things I’d recommend 👇
🍎 Make the switch from UPF to whole foods where possible. Not only will this keep you more satiated, but your body uses more energy in the digestion process. 
🍎 Meal timings has been shown to affect your hunger cues, so start by bringing your dinner time forward by 1 hour.
🍎 Keep the skin on your foods (like your kiwi fruit, sweet potatoes etc) as this contains extra fibre which helps to stimulate the release of the appetite regulating GLP-1 hormone.

For the past two and a half decades, I’ve primarily worn Mara Hoffman or second-hand/vintage pieces. Stepping away from producing my own collections has opened up a new world of exploration into my personal relationship with clothes, fashion, and acquiring new things. 

While it was incredible to create what I wanted to wear season after season, I’ve recently been enjoying the freedom of discovering the visions of others, especially those whose values align with mine. I’m especially grateful for my dear friend @vanessaanabarboni , founder of @anothertomorrow . Their commitment to sustainability and ethical practices is the real deal as are their beautiful and timeless designs. There’s nothing easy about running a brand built on the ethos of doing the least harm while also trying to improve and create new systems of repair and care within a broken industry.

Visiting her stunning new flagship store in SoHo reminded me why I love clothes—the joy they bring, especially when made with integrity and respect for our planet.

At the end of the day, do I really need anything new? Probably not. But I still find immense joy in expressing myself through fashion and appreciate exquisite craftsmanship that’s done with care. Another Tomorrow is a brand that I believe is paving the way for a more conscious future in fashion. I’m excited to support their mission and have a ton of respect for the people in this industry who are doing the good work. ❤️

It was a true honor to photograph the incredible Waorani leader @nemonte.nenquimo for the newest issue of @one_magazine where she is in conversation with @cameronrussell ❤️

📖 Nemonte’s new book, co-authored with her husband and @amazonfrontlines co-founder @mitchandersonaf , “We Will Be Jaguars,” is a powerful memoir that chronicles her journey as an indigenous leader and advocate for the Amazon rainforest. This extraordinary book is a call to protect the #AmazonRainforest—the jaguar’s home and a vital lifeline for our planet. 🌿🐆 

Indigenous women like Nemonte are courageously standing on the frontlines, defending the rainforest from oil extraction, mining, logging, and the devastating effects of climate change.

Today also marks National Jaguar Day. For every copy of Nemonte’s book sold today, $10 will be donated to Amazon Frontlines, supporting their mission to defend the rainforest, the true home of the jaguar. 

Consider this a meaningful alternative to Black Friday. Together, we can stand in solidarity with the Amazon and its guardians. 💚

It happened! 🦄✨The unicorn of real estate in 2024. 
Let me explain…

When Zac and I first met up in March to discuss the buying process, I was very straight forward. It is TOUGH out here for buyers. After going through everything step by step, I let him know the reality of winning your first offer, or even your second and third, is slim.

Well don’t you know, Zac goes and proves me wrong.

I’ve never been happier to be wrong in my life.

Zac and I went and looked at [T H R E E] houses and we put in [O N E] offer. I’ll be honest, Zac knew what he wanted and wasn’t afraid to fight for it. His offer was very aggressive and when it came down for all the best offers to be submitted, he stayed firm with his original terms… and won!! 🎉 This is the perfect example of price not being the only important factor. There were offers slightly higher, but our terms were 🤌🏼.

So, here’s to Zac, with the most seamless transaction since I started in real estate 🥂!!! I’m so happy for you.

This CHICKEN & PROSCIUTTO TORTELLONI WITH WHITE WINE CREAM SAUCE is perfect for those nights when you want a fancy meal in less than 30 minutes!

You’ll need…⁠
9 oz BUITONI Chicken & Prosciutto Tortelloni  2 Tbsp butter⁠
1 Tbsp flour⁠
3 cloves garlic minced⁠
1/2 cup dry white wine⁠
¾ cup heavy cream⁠
1/2 cup BUITONI Parmesan Cheese⁠
1-2 tablespoons parsley, chopped⁠
Salt & pepper to taste⁠

Directions: ⁠
MELT butter to pan over medium heat. Sprinkle flour and cook for 1-2 minutes until golden brown.⁠
ADD garlic and white wine. Let bubble and reduce by half. Whisk in heavy cream. Take sauce off the heat and add parmesan. Stir to melt and combine. ⁠
PREPARE tortelloni according to package directions. Reserve ¼ cup pasta water.⁠
ADD cooked tortelloni to the sauce and place back on the heat and add reserved pasta water as needed to thin out sauce. ⁠
TOP with parsley to serve.

TIMESAVER:  Warm BUITONI Alfredo Sauce in a small saucepan over medium heat.  Stir in ½ cup dry white wine.

10-MINUTE BUITONI TORTELLINI AND CHEESE is definitely for cheese lovers and with only 3 ingredients it’s an easy meal for anyone! 🧀💚

You’ll need...⁠
9 oz BUITONI Three Cheese Tortellini⁠
1/2 container BUITONI Alfredo Sauce⁠
1/2 cup mozzarella cheese⁠
⁠
Directions:
PREPARE tortellini according to package directions.⁠
OVER medium heat, add Alfredo sauce and mozzarella cheese. Stir frequently until sauce is heated through and cheese is melty.
ADD cooked tortellini and stir to combine.

7.25 oz roasted red peppers, drained
¾ cup heavy cream
1/2 package @boursincheese Garlic & Herb Cheese
1/4 cup BUITONI Shredded Parmesan Cheese
Salt and Pepper, to taste

Directions:
PLACE peppers and heavy cream in a blender or food processor; cover and pulse until smooth.
ADD red pepper sauce, 1/2 slice Boursin cheese puck in pan over low-medium heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted and cooked through. Be sure NOT to boil. 
COOK fettuccine according to package directions and add to the sauce. Toss to coat. Serve with BUITONI Parmesan cheese and serve.

ALFREDO CORN SOUP is the perfect blend of creamy comfort and sweet corn goodness in every bite! 🌽✨

You’ll need…
3 Tbsp olive oil
1 yellow onion, chopped
2 carrots, chopped
2 celery ribs, chopped
2 large russet potatoes, cubed
2 cups chicken broth 
Salt & pepper to taste
3-4 whole corn ears, kernels cut off
1 zucchini, cubed
1 BUITONI Alfredo Sauce

Directions:
ADD olive oil, onion, carrots and celery in a large pot. Stir and cook for 5 mins. Add in potatoes, salt and pepper and cook for 8-10 more minutes. Add in chicken broth, corn, and zucchini.
REDUCE heat to low, cover and cook for an additional 10 mins. Add in BUITONI Alfredo, salt and pepper. Stir to combine.
REMOVE from pot 2 cups of chowder and blend. Once pureed return to pot. Stir to combine and serve hot.
Red team or White team? Which one are you on? Tell us in the comments! 👇

This RAVIOLI LASAGNA SOUP is cozy, hearty, and oh-so-satisfying! 🥰 

You’ll need…
2 Tbsp olive oil 
1 cup white onion, diced
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 lb ground sausage
6 oz can tomato paste
2- 14.5 oz cans fire roasted diced tomatoes
32 oz chicken stock
20 oz BUITONI Four Cheese Ravioli 
¼ cup fresh chopped parsley 
2 cups ricotta cheese
1 cup grated parmesan cheese
Salt and pepper

Directions:
PLACE oil in a large pot and add onions stirring until softened. Add garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add ground sausage and cook until browned.
ADD in tomato paste, fire roasted tomatoes and chicken broth, stirring to combine. Bring to a simmer and add ravioli, salt and pepper to taste. Cook for at least 5 minutes. Reduce heat and add fresh parsley.
COMBINE ricotta, parmesan, salt and pepper in a small bowl. 
ADD soup to bowl and dollop a spoonful of ricotta mixture on top to serve.

Creamy, dreamy, cheesy perfection! 😍 This CHICKEN  & ROASTED GARLIC TORTELLONI BAKE is comfort food goals. Who’s hungry?! 

You’ll need…
20 oz BUITONI Chicken & Roasted Garlic Tortellini 
6-8 strips bacon, cut into small pieces
1-2 cloves garlic, minced
¼ cup chicken broth
1 cup heavy cream
4 oz cream cheese, softened
Salt and pepper
½ cup BUITONI Shredded Parmesan Cheese
1 cup mozzarella 

Directions:⁠
HEAT oven to 400° F and spray 8”x 8” baking dish with non-stick cooking spray. Set aside.⁠
CUT bacon into small pieces and cook in a large pan with 1 Tbsp of olive oil. ⁠
COOK until crispy and remove from pan and place on a paper towel lined plate. Set aside, leaving about 2 Tbsp of the bacon fat in the pan.  ⁠TURN off the heat, add garlic, chicken broth, heavy cream and cream cheese to the pan. Turn heat back to low and stir until cheese is melted and bubbly. Stir in BUITONI Shredded Parmesan and bacon ⁠
PREPARE tortelloni according to package directions, drain and add to sauce.⁠
ADD the prepared tortelloni into prepared baking dish. Top with mozzarella and bake for 15-20 minutes or until cheesy in melted and bubbly.⁠

15-MINUTE CACIO E PEPE TORTELLINI is a twist on the delicious classic for when you’re feeling a little extra! 🤩⁠
⁠
You’ll need…⁠
9 oz BUITONI Three Cheese Tortellini ⁠
2 Tbsp butter⁠
½ cup finely chopped white onion⁠
1 large clove garlic, finely minced⁠
3 Tbsp all purpose flour⁠
1 cup low-fat milk ⁠
1 cup chicken broth ⁠
1/2 cup Pecorino Romano ⁠
1/3 cup BUITONI Parmesan Cheese ⁠
1-2 tsp fresh cracked or coarse pepper ⁠
⁠
Directions:⁠
MELT butter in pot over medium-high heat. Add in onions and cook, stirring frequently until nearly soft.
ADD in garlic and flour, and cook for about 1 minute. Pour in milk and chicken broth. Bring to a simmer and continue to cook until thickened.⁠
COOK tortellini according to package directions, drain, and reserve ¼ cup pasta water.
REMOVE sauce from heat and stir in Romano cheese and Parmesan cheese and pepper mixing until melted and combined. ⁠
ADD cooked tortellini. Stir to combine. Add reserved pasta water as needed.

This BUITONI SPAGHETTI BAKE is jam-packed with classic Italian flavors baked right in! 🤩

You’ll need:
2-9 oz BUITONI Spaghetti packs
15 oz BUITONI Alfredo sauce
¼ cup water
15 oz BUITONI Meat Sauce
2 cups Mozzarella Cheese 
⅓ cup grated Parmesan cheese
Chopped parsley
Salt and pepper to taste

Directions:
HEAT oven to 400° F.
PREPARE both spaghetti packages according to package instructions and drain.
POUR BUITONI Alfredo sauce in a large skillet over medium heat. Add water to sauce container, close, and shake to get remaining sauce. Place into the pan and add prepared spaghetti. Toss thoroughly to coat.
ADD Alfredo spaghetti evenly into a 9X13” baking dish. Spread BUITONI Meat sauce on top. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
BAKE for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly. Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes. Top with parsley. Cut in squares and serve hot.

RAVIOLI WITH ROASTED GARLIC SAUCE is for *serious* garlic lovers only! 🥰🧄

You’ll need…
1/2 cup of peeled garlic (seek out pre-peeled garlic for convenience)
3/4 cups olive oil
15 oz BUITONI Marinara Sauce
20 oz BUITONI Four Cheese Ravioli
BUITONI Parmesan cheese, to serve

Directions:
HEAT the oven to 300° F. Add garlic to a roasting dish, then cover with olive oil. Cook for 45 minutes to an hour, or until garlic is very tender.⁠ Drain and reserve 2 Tbsp olive oil. Place extra oil in an airtight container in the refrigerator for near future use. 
COOK ravioli according to package instructions. Drain and reserve ½ cup pasta water. 
ADD garlic to a pan over medium heat and mash. Pour in BUITONI Marinara Sauce and bring to a simmer⁠.
ADD in cooked ravioli and pasta water as needed. Sprinkle in BUITONI Parmesan Cheese and mix well to melt cheese.

Dive into a buttery flaky delight filled with rich BUITONI Alfredo goodness with CHICKEN ALFREDO CROISSANTS! 😍

You’ll need…
2 cups shredded chicken
1 cups shredded mozzarella cheese 
1 tsp Basil
1 cup BUITONI Alfredo Sauce
¼ cup grated Parmesan Cheese
Refrigerated Croissant rolls
2 Tbsp butter, melted
1 garlic clove, minced
⅛ tsp red crushed pepper 

Directions:
HEAT oven to 375°.
ADD shredded chicken, mozzarella, Parmesan, basil and BUITONI Alfredo in a large bowl. Mix to thoroughly combine. 
LAY out individual croissant triangles on a lined baking sheet. Add 1-2 Tbsp of filling in each wide end of the croissant. Roll from the wide end toward the narrow. Pinch ends closed.
COMBINE combining melted butter, garlic and red pepper and brush on top of rolls. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on each.
BAKE for 18-25 mins or until golden brown. 
SERVE with additional BUITONI Alfredo sauce for dipping.

Stage 6 Done with Mixed Results! 🔥

Provisional Rankings - Stage 06
P3 - @nachocornejo11 
DNF - @rossbranchbw

Continuing his impressive form, Nacho crossed the finish line today with the 3rd fastest time, missing the stage win by just 51 seconds - and has now climbed up to the 8th spot in the overall rankings.

Sadly, for Ross Branch, the Dakar 2025 journey came to an end today as the Botswanan hero met with an unfortunate crash at 48 km into today’s stage. After an immediate medical check-up, he was airlifted to the Ha’il hospital where his CT scan came out clear and revealed no major injuries. Ross has been discharged from the hospital and has joined the team tonight. 

Branch had been delivering a stellar performance right since the start of the rally, holding 4th place overall until his untimely exit. The 2024 World Rally-Raid Champion and last year's Dakar Rally runner-up will now shift his focus to recovery and is determined to come back stronger for the next race of the World Championship. 

Cornejo will now be leading the charge for the team, carrying the mantle forward in the rally and has his sights set on getting a respectable Dakar finish for the team this year. 

Today’s Stage 6 of the rally presented a unique challenge, spanning 605 km and divided into two segments. A 171 km untimed road section, classified as a "transfer," separated the two parts, resulting in 434 km of timed competition. 

Tomorrow’s Stage 7 with 455 km of timed specials will make the rally more challenging with a good mix of fast and slow terrains, difficult navigation and a touch of mountain racing as well. Tomorrow’s stage will start slightly later to allow enough time for the helicopters to reach their respective positions after their multiple deployments for race safety today.

The memes flood in—“Spotify exposing me again!”—as if they didn’t curate every second of it themselves. Michael’s boundless enthusiasm and lack of self-awareness set the stage, while Jim’s deadpan sarcasm keeps it grounded—until Dwight, with his unrelenting intensity and bizarre logic, blows it all out of proportion. Together, they’re an unstoppable force of cringe-worthy comedy and unexpected teamwork. Whether it’s Jim teaming up with Michael to outmaneuver Dwight or all three uniting for a shared goal (usually involving some absurd office mission), their dynamic is as unpredictable as it is hilarious. Michael’s misguided attempts to be the “world’s best boss” often turn into a circus, with Dwight acting as his loyal enforcer and Jim subtly steering things in a less disastrous direction. And yet, when they manage to align their chaotic energy, the results are oddly effective, like the time they band together to land a big client or pull off a ridiculous party. Their chemistry thrives in the tension between Jim’s cool detachment, Dwight’s obsessive dedication, and Michael’s over-the-top antics. It’s not just about the laughs—they’re a reminder that even the most mismatched personalities can create something unforgettable when they come together.

Hanging out with her for the first time feels like a chance you don’t want to mess up, so you plan every detail, even down to the playlist. You remember that one song she posted on her Instagram story 43 weeks ago, and you queue it up, hoping it’ll subtly impress her. When it starts playing, you glance at her face, pretending it’s just a random pick, but secretly hoping she notices. Her eyes light up, and she asks how you know that song, her voice a mix of curiosity and surprise. You shrug casually, trying not to give away the hours you spent scrolling through her profile, and say, “I just thought you might like it.” The moment feels small but meaningful, as if you’ve cracked a secret code that sets you apart. She smiles, and you can tell she’s intrigued, like maybe you’re not just another guy after all. It’s a risk that could’ve come off as too much, but instead, it feels like the perfect way to show her you’re paying attention in a world where so many don’t.

Defending your best friend, even when you know they probably did whatever they’re being accused of, is a unique mix of loyalty and mental gymnastics. You find yourself coming up with every excuse in the book, hoping to shift the blame just enough to make them look better. “Well, they didn’t mean it like that,” or “You don’t even know the whole story,” becomes your go-to response, even if you’re not entirely sure what the whole story is yourself. Deep down, you’re side-eyeing them like, Seriously? Again? but on the outside, you’re their biggest supporter. If someone pushes back too hard, you double down, because nobody else is allowed to call them out except you. You know they probably deserve some of the heat, but you also know their heart and intentions, even if their execution is a mess. Later, when it’s just the two of you, you’ll give them a piece of your mind for putting you in the line of fire. But in the moment, you’ll defend them to the end, because that’s what best friends do, even when they make it hard.

Ranging from shimmering pinks to deep, blood reds, rubies have captured hearts and imaginations around the globe for centuries. Our client sought a bold, beautiful design—and the InBloom Jewelry team delivered. The result? A stunning ruby ring from our Leaves Collection, featuring 14k yellow gold sage leaves that perfectly complement the gem’s vibrant hue.

Throughout history, rubies have been steeped in symbolism. In Medieval England, they were associated with royalty and believed to bring wealth and success in love. In ancient India, their fiery color symbolized power, energy, and the vital life force within us. Sage leaves, likewise, carry profound meaning, often used in Native American traditions to cleanse negative energy and restore balance.

Nature’s emblems—plants, gemstones, and animals—are rich with significance. At InBloom Jewelry, we love weaving these meaningful elements into our designs, creating pieces that tell a unique story for each wearer.

بلومبرگ گزارش داده است که بازگشت ترامپ به سیاست فشار حداکثری می‌تواند صادرات نفت جمهوری اسلامی را به حدود ۴۰۰ هزار بشکه در روز کاهش دهد و سالانه ۳۰ میلیارد دلار از درآمدهای نفتی این کشور بکاهد. این اقدام که با اعمال تحریم‌های جدید از فوریه ممکن است آغاز شود، ۷ درصد از تولید ناخالص داخلی ایران را تحت تأثیر قرار خواهد داد.
در دوره بایدن، جمهوری اسلامی با کاهش فشار تحریم‌ها صادرات نفت خود را به ۱.۶ میلیون بشکه در روز رساند و توانست حدود ۱۴۰ میلیارد دلار نفت به چین بفروشد. اما کارشناسان پیش‌بینی می‌کنند با اجرای تحریم‌های ترامپ، صادرات نفت به چین تا تابستان حدود یک میلیون بشکه کاهش یابد. این محدودیت‌ها در شرایطی رخ می‌دهد که اقتصاد ایران با افت ارزش پول ملی، کمبود سوخت و بحران زیرساخت‌های برق مواجه است.

شاهزاده رضا پهلوی در پیامی ویدئویی از ایرانیان خواست با خرید عضویت در کانال یوتیوب تلویزیون منوتو از این شبکه حمایت کنند. 

او گفت: «خیلی از رسانه‌ها با بودجه‌های دولتی و برای دولت‌های دیگر کار می‌کنند. نهادها و رسانه‌های مستقل نقش بسیار حائز اهمیتی از این لحاظ دارند و شبکه منوتو یکی از آنها است.» شاهزاده رضا پهلوی در ادامه افزود: «من خودم عضو کانال یوتیوب منوتو هستم و فکر می‌کنم از این طریق کمک خودم را به این رسانه می‌رسانم. امیدوار هستم شما نیز به سهم خودتان از این رسانه حمایت کنید».

بهای دلار در بازار ارز ایران امروز چهارم بهمن‌ماه از مرز ۸۴ هزار تومان عبور کرد. همچنین سکه طلا نیز بالای ۶۰ میلیون تومان معامله می‌شود. سیر صعودی بهای ارز در ایران که در هفته‌های اخیر شدت گرفته بود با آغاز دوره ریاست‌جمهوری دونالد ترامپ بیشتر شده است.

گزارشگرمنوتو: «وظیفه ملی خودم میدونم در این اتحاد ملی شریک بشم» 
منوتو فراتر از سرگرمی

‌
مسعود پزشکیان در بخشی از سخنرامی امروز چهارم بهمن‌ماه از یک ضرب‌المثل ترکی استفاده کرد. او بعد از گفتن این ضرب‌المثل ترجمه‌اش را چنین گفت: «بچه اگر شعور داشته باشد، دارایی را می‌خواهد چه‌ کار؟ اگر بیشعور هم باشد دارایی را برای چه می‌خواهد؟»

مدیرکل میراث فرهنگی، گردشگری و صنایع‌دستی گیلان از خسارت دو میلیارد تومانی به «میل املش» در پی آتش‌سوزی اخیر و آزادی فرد خاطی با وثیقه تا زمان برگزاری دادگاه خبر داد.
در روزهای گذشته، آتش زدن میل تاریخی روستای اُمام از توابع شهرستان املش واکنش‌های گسترده‌ای را برانگیخته است. بر اساس گزارش‌ها، فردی که ابتدا به عنوان بلاگر معرفی شده بود، برای جذب دنبال‌کننده در فضای مجازی، این اثر تاریخی را به آتش کشیده است.
پس از انتشار تصاویر این آتش‌سوزی، مقامات میراث فرهنگی اعلام کردند که عامل این حادثه توسط نیروهای انتظامی دستگیر شده است. با این حال، متهم پس از یک شب بازداشت، با قرار وثیقه آزاد شد و پرونده او در انتظار رأی دادگاه است.

روزنامه بریتانیایی «فایننشال تایمز» به نقل از «منابع امنیتی دو کشور غربی» گزارش داد که دو کشتی ایرانی حامل بیش از هزار تن مواد لازم برای تهیه سوخت جامد موشک‌، در حال حرکت از چین به سوی ایران هستند.
براساس این گزارش و اطلاعات امنیتی دو کشور غربی پیش‌بینی می‌شود کشتی‌های ایرانی «گلبن» و «جیران»، حامل محموله‌ای بیش از هزار تن «سدیم پرکلرات»، ماده اصلی در تولید سوخت جامد موشکی «آمونیوم پرکلرات»، باشند.
سدیم پرکلرات می‌تواند ۹۶۰ تن آمونیوم پرکلرات تولید کند؛ مقداری که برای ساخت ۱۳۰۰ تن پیشرانه موشکی کافی است و می‌تواند ۲۶۰ موشک میان‌برد ایرانی را تأمین سوخت کند.
به گفته این دو مقام، سدیم پرکلرات برای سپاه ارسال می‌شود و ۳۴ کانتینر «شش متری» حاوی این ماده شیمیایی، روی کشتی گلبن بارگیری شده است. 
این کشتی سه‌شنبه جزیره دایشان در چین را ترک کرده است.

.
این زلزله در حوالی شهر ریز در شهرستان جم استان بوشهر رخ داد و در مناطق جنوبی استان نیز احساس شد. پس از وقوع زلزله، دو تیم ارزیاب هلال‌احمر به منطقه اعزام شدند تا از خسارات احتمالی بازدید کنند. 
تا کنون گزارشی از تلفات جانی یا خسارات مالی منتشر نشده است.

آتش‌سوزی گسترده‌ای در سن‌دیگو، کالیفرنیا آغاز شده است که تاکنون بخش‌های وسیعی از مناطق جنگلی و مسکونی را تهدید کرده است. تیم‌های آتش‌نشانی با تمام توان در تلاش هستند تا شعله‌های آتش را مهار کنند. وزش بادهای شدید و خشکی هوا کار مهار آتش را دشوار کرده است. مقامات محلی از ساکنان خواسته‌اند تا مناطق پرخطر را تخلیه کنند. جزئیات بیشتری درباره خسارات احتمالی و تعداد تخلیه‌شدگان هنوز منتشر نشده است.

آتش‌سوزی‌های جدیدی که در نزدیکی لس‌آنجلس آغاز شده، به سرعت گسترش یافته است. به دلیل شدت آتش، آسمان به رنگ قرمز درآمده و دستور تخلیه اجباری برای ۳۱۰۰۰ نفر از ساکنان مناطق مجاور صادر شده است. شرایط به شدت بحرانی است و تلاش‌ها برای مهار آتش ادامه دارد.

آتش‌سوزی جدیدی که روز چهارشنبه در شمال لس‌آنجلس آغاز شد، به سرعت به بیش از ۹۴۰۰ هکتار گسترش یافت. این آتش‌سوزی که با وزش بادهای شدید و پوشش گیاهی خشک تغذیه می‌شود، باعث صدور دستور تخلیه اجباری برای بیش از ۳۱۰۰۰ نفر از ساکنان مناطق اطراف شد. آتش‌سوزی هیوز که حدود ۸۰ کیلومتری شمال لس‌آنجلس در حال پیشروی است، فشار بیشتری بر آتش‌نشانان منطقه وارد کرده است، با این حال آن‌ها توانسته‌اند دو آتش‌سوزی بزرگ دیگر در این منطقه را تا حد زیادی تحت کنترل درآورند.

Photo by @ronan_donovan | I recall a moment, suspended in the dim firelight of the high Arctic, when Clean Coat, the alpha male of the Polygon pack, tested a prime-age bull musk ox. The encounter was brief, barely more than a flicker in time, but within the swirling clouds of dust, there was something vast, an ancient knowing exchanged between them. In the space between their eyes, between each calculated breath, a quiet understanding passed—wordless, elemental, older than the tundra itself. What seemed like a fleeting test of strength held the weight of millennia, carried in every particle of dust that hovered in the still air.

The dance between predator and prey is an ancient, primal rhythm, a choreography etched into the bones of the earth. For millions of years, this exchange has unfolded, each step imbued with a quiet inevitability—the survival of one relies on the death of the other. But the predator does not simply hunt; it seeks to claim its place, to assert itself in the ongoing story of life. The prey calls upon a trembling strength, a resistance as old as the hunt itself, each sinew taut with purpose. In this timeless ritual, neither truly leads or follows. There is only the enduring balance, the unspoken understanding that both are bound by something larger than hunger or fear.

Photo by @joelsartore | Found on every continent except Antarctica and South America, moles like this eastern mole at Nebraska Wildlife Rehab are often viewed as garden pests because of the intricate underground tunnel systems they construct. Such behavior may label moles as a backyard nuisance, but they actually play a beneficial role in soil management and controlling the population of undesirable grubs and insects. By digging and moving earth, moles permit better aeration of the soil and enable organic matter to travel deeper down. Their tunneling also allows subsoil material to be moved closer to the surface, where nutrients may be more available to plant roots. National Geographic photographers ventured to places far and wide to capture the year’s most fascinating images. Out of more than 2.3 million photos, 20 were selected as our Pictures of the Year. See them all at the link in bio.

📸 1 - Jasper Doest (@jasperdoest) was documenting international efforts to protect transborder wildlife corridors when he heard that an elephant had been killed on a nearby highway. In Zambia, climate change is forcing humans and wildlife to compete for the same resources, and the situation is becoming increasingly tense—but despite this adversarial relationship, there was still a sense of awe among bystanders, many of whom had never seen an elephant so close. 

📸 2 - Ryan Tidman (@ryantidman) photographed Pacific herring spawning off the coast of Vancouver Island. Every spring, females release up to 20,000 eggs each, and then males release milt (semen)—an event that offers both a visual spectacle and a valuable food source for animals like this nearby sea lion.

📸 3 - Peter Fisher (@pet__fish) captured an image of a volcanic eruption in Guatemala. Fuego Volcano erupts multiple times a day—and a hike up its dormant neighbor, Acatenango, offers visitors a front-row seat to this remarkable phenomenon.

Photo by @mattiasklumofficial | This orangutan at the Nyaru Menteng Rehabilitation Center in Indonesian Borneo is a lucky one. Female orangutans are often killed when confronted in oil palm plantations or logged areas and their babies kept as illegal pets. Many of these orphans die of starvation. But if rescued by NGOs specializing in rehabilitating orangutans to return them to the wild, they have a fighting chance. Many are deeply traumatized by having seen their mothers killed, and some can never be let back into the wild.

In the wild, black vultures will hatch one brood per breeding season, laying their eggs just about anywhere—from the hollow bases of trees to cliff edges to holes under rocks. Unlike many birds, they do not use materials to build their nests. Once eggs are laid, both parents will take turns incubating them for up to 41 days until they hatch. 🏠Why PadSplit has survived as our competitors shut their doors… 🏢

1️⃣👷‍♀️ We remain committed to serving frontline workers.

While other coliving companies chased after affluent millennials in high-cost urban centers, we recognized the massive housing need for frontline workers across urban typologies. PadSplit units typically rent for $600-800 per month on average, including utilities, far less than others in co-living.

2️⃣💼 PadSplit is an asset-light, sustainable business model

Many of the coliving companies that failed appeared to take on too much financial risk and overhead through excessive leasing of properties or expensive build-outs. By contrast, we’ve taken an asset-light approach by aligning incentives with property owners.

Renting by the room is and always has been a more profitable business than renting entire houses or apartments. But it’s also a lot more work. PadSplit was created to provide the services and technology that most housing providers either cannot provide on their own or simply don’t want to deal with.

3️⃣🤝 A resilient team and company culture

A successful business is about more than just numbers and models - it’s about the people behind it. Our mission to “solve the affordable housing crisis while leveraging housing as a vehicle for financial empowerment” has played an enormous role in our ability to attract and retain outstanding talent.

We’re incredibly privileged to work alongside some amazing people who likely wouldn’t be here if they weren’t confident in our mission. Seeing and hearing the intensely personal stories of transformation through housing inspires us all.

4️⃣🚀 Major plans to scale

We have major expansion plans in the pipeline, with new markets we’ll be entering and new products we’ll be rolling out. We’re also investing heavily in technology to streamline operations and provide even better service to our residents and partners.

We hope other coliving companies enter the market, even if they are directly competitive with us because we are a social impact-focused company. We believe we need more smart people in this space to attack the many issues and rise all tides.

I’m to a point where the dividends generated from my investments produce almost as much annual income as my actual W-2 job! It’s a nice place to be that both provides more income and diversification of income in case I lose my job!

How do I do this?! Basically I have a lot of money invested. About $3 million sitting in index funds right now. Index funds are paying about a 2% annual dividend at the moment. 2% of $3M = $60K/year of free money.

How did I get to $3M invested?! A large part of it came from when I was fortunate enough to sell a company I started in college. That provided a windfall of about $2M. That $2M has since grown to over $5M (the rest of that money in my house and some other investments).

It’s easy to write this off as “oh, he just sold a company”. That’s partially true for sure, but before, during, and after selling the company I was also doing some important personal finance things. Specifically, I was living below my means and investing early and often. If at the age of 34 when I sold my company, I decided to start living like a baller in Southern California, I’m quite sure I could have spent through that $2M by now. Instead, I decided to put that money to WORK to provide income for the rest of my life!

Dividends are obviously great because they represent cash deposits into your account without having to sell any shares! But should you CHASE dividends? i.e. should you be buying stocks or funds that produce high dividends to get MORE of them? In my opinion: No. Buying stuff that produces more dividends is just asking for more of your growth to be immediately taxable to you and you’re likely omitting more quickly growing companies. For example last year, Vanguard’s dividend ETF (VYM) had total growth of about 17% compared to their growth ETF (VGT) which had total growth of about 29%. I don’t buy VGT either... I buy BOTH in a total market fund, like VTI!

I often get asked, “what is the best index fund?” And the answer is “it doesn’t really matter." There aren’t “good” or “bad” index funds. They all do the same thing and that’s the point. They follow the index they’re assigned to. And all the little details just don’t matter that much.‎
‎
The twelve index fund listed here are kind of a mixed bag: ‎
‎
• 7 are mutual funds, 5 are ETFs. ‎
• 7 follow 500 of the biggest stocks. 1 follows 1,000 stocks. Four follow the total stock market (~4,000 stocks)‎
• They’re offered by a bunch of different companies (Vanguard, Fidelity, Schwab, iShares/Blackrock, State Street)‎
• Their expense ratios range from 0.015% (FXAIX and FSKAX) to 0.14% (VFINX). ‎
‎
With all those differences, they all essentially do the same thing. Own a bunch of US stock. EVEN the fact that some follow 4,000+ stocks vs others follow only 500 doesn’t make a big difference (for those asking me S&P 500 vs total market).‎
‎
With all those differences, and after over 13 years of tracking them the top performing index fund outperformed the lowest performing one by growing the $10,000 to $60,686 versus $57,668. Not a big deal.‎
‎
It turns out the S&P 500 index funds all outperformed the total market index funds by about 4% over this time. That doesn’t mean that trend will continue in the future (I actually expect it won’t), rather I think it reflects that large companies fared slightly better than small ones during the pandemic and AI tech boom.‎
‎
And if you want to know which one actually performed the best. Drumroll… It was, surprise surprise, the one with the lowest expense ratio (0.015%): FXAIX (Fidelity 500 Index Fund).‎
‎
The moral of the story is don’t get caught up in the weeds. Don’t worry about which exact index fund to buy, just pick one with a low expense ratio and spend your effort plowing more money into it.‎

This is an annual recurring event on my actual calendar. These are the few financial things I make sure to take care of at the beginning of each year. To break them down:

 • I’m almost always over the Roth IRA income limit, so I do a “backdoor” Roth IRA which consists of contributing to a Traditional IRA, then converting it to a Roth IRA. The max you can contribute to an IRA in 2025 is $7,000. (I have a video on Backdoor Roth IRAs in my course and an article on my website).
 • HSAs have the best tax advantage of any account! Money goes in tax-free, investments grow tax-free, and money spent on qualified medical expenses is tax-free! I keep mine with Fidelity. I keep about $2K in cash to cover current medical expenses, the rest I invest in a target date index fund.
• Keep in mind putting money in an IRA or HSA alone doesn’t do anything. You have to take the second step and invest that money! I invest mine in index funds.
• My dead box is a Google Drive folder with a list of accounts and instructions to help unwind my financial life in the unlikely event of my untimely demise. I go through and update this every January. It’s amazing what changes over a year!
• The dead box is no good if no one knows where to find it, so I email my wife and brother (will executors) to remind them it’s there and how to get to it.
• They say that “numbers that are tracked improve”. I’ve been tracking my net worth since I was 20 when it was about $5,000. It dropped to -$5,000 by age 22, but today it’s about $5.3 Million.

My Roth IRA is currently worth about $147K and my HSA has $35K. That amount plus the annual contributions invested at an 8% rate of return will be worth over $2.1M in 25 years!

I see lots of posts and headlines like this, except they're serious. I just saw one and I rolled my eyes so hard that I sprained my eyeballs. And when I got back from the optometrist, I charged back here to remind you that this kind of stuff is NOT REAL. 

Investing is NOT picking the next hot stock and getting rich quick. That's gambling. And it works out about as well as going to Vegas. It’s important to note that what Brittany (and Tiffany!) did is totally impossible. NOBODY knows when the top or bottom of the market will be. YET STILL, even though Brittany had IMPOSSIBLY PERFECT timing, she still lost to Sarah. That tells an important lesson. EVEN IF YOU GET THE TIMING RIGHT, while you’re sitting on the sidelines waiting to “buy the dip” the early and often investor will be building a lead you’ll never overcome. 

There’s an even more important lesson here: ALL THREE OF THESE INVESTORS ARE RICH. Even “terrible” Tiffany is a multi-millionaire! Why? Because once she got in the market she practiced BUY AND HOLD investing. She bought, held, and let the market do its work for decades. So even though she had IMPOSSIBLY BAD timing, the very simple practice of buy and hold made her rich.

@bambambaklava and @newbalance have been on a hot streak since first teaming up in 2023. Their partnership began two years ago with a bold arrangement featuring 990v6 and they went on to release a “Lapis Lazuli” pair later that year, as well as teased a yellow and gray iteration that has yet to resurface.⁠
⁠
Now, after a teaser of a “Hi-Pink” pair was shared previously, we have our best look yet at a brown, pink and blue iteration that made an appearance in Bronson’s recent BAKLAVA lookbook. @richardmille is continuing to push boundaries with the unveiling of the RM 16-02 Automatic Extraflat. Combining technical sophistication with bold, minimalist aesthetics, the timepiece reimagines Richard Mille’s signature style with a rectangular, monolithic design that embodies brutalist architecture. Clean geometric lines provide elegance while the skeletonized CRMA9 in-house movement, crafted from grade 5 titanium, reveals the intricate engineering beneath its surface.⁠
⁠
At just 4.12 mm thick, the extraflat movement features a free-sprung balance with variable inertia, ensuring greater reliability and precision over time. The timepiece additionally boasts 50 hours of power reserve and is water resistant up to 30 meters.⁠
⁠
For those interested, the RM 16-02 Automatic Extraflat is available now with price available upon request.⁠
Photo: Richard Mille

@hypeform: Japanese design firm @igaarchitects has designed this unique residence, dubbed the Pyramid Hut. Situated on a long, narrow plot of land, the property has a secluded feel as it is surrounded on three sides by apartments and a cemetery, providing dense plant life. Due to the unique setting, the design choice steered away from an “Okinawa-like” building and instead pulled inspiration from traditional Okinawan tombs.⁠
⁠
The space features a square pyramid structure, elevated from a solid foundation of Ryukyu limestone. Limited openings in the foundation and a roof surface allow for controlled connections to the exterior while still maintaining a peaceful and tranquil living environment within the home.⁠
⁠
Interior-wise, the home is split into three distinct levels. The first includes the bathroom and entrance while the second houses the living and dining room along with a study. Meanwhile, the third level at the back contains the bedroom and other private spaces.⁠
⁠
Swipe to get a closer look at the home.⁠
Photo: IGArchitects

⁠
Available in six colorways, the iPod Nano-inspired design at five feet tall and emulates the exact structure of Apple’s now-discontinued portable media player and retails for $375 USD. ⁠
⁠
The iPod Nano’s circular remote rests at the bottom in its classic white color, with the top function on the remote replaced to read “Drought.” The song playing on each of the six colorways is entitled “Find Yourself,” while the top of the screen reads “Now Living” and the backside “iReflect” alongside Drought’s logo.⁠
⁠
With only 200 units made, expect the collection to be available on January 24 at 12pm EST.⁠
Photo: Drought

It’s been 20 years since @nike first teamed up with @ohsudoernbecher to create a collection of sneakers designed by patients. The program has raised $40 million USD in its two decades of running and has seen 122 patient-designers create one-of-a-kind kicks with the help of 330 Nike volunteer product experts. Now, it’s finally time for the 20th collection to hit shelves.⁠
⁠
Each shoe embodies the personality and journey of these children and, for the first time, will come in a special custom, split-open box. First up, Connor Kassing Fernández’s Air Max Dn shines bright in black and gold as nods to his love for music and Spanish heritage are sprinkled in throughout. From there, the AJ6 celebrates Jillian Beagley’s love for basketball with a mismatched colorway that hosts interchangeable patches of her favorite things at the collar. Quin Nims reworked the Air Max Sunder, bringing a dragon scale-inspired pattern to its special spiky mudguard shape. As for basketball aficionado Sophia Jenkins, her Sabrina 2 commemorates the many things that bring her comfort in life. As for Tima Sviridenko’s Air Zoom Pegasus 41, it draws much of its inspiration from his love for cats. Lastly, Ja’Kai Taylor took on the Air 180, presenting a video game-inspired blue-green gradient across its upper.⁠
⁠
Release for all six shoes is confirmed to take place on January 25 with prices ranging from $130 USD to $200 USD.⁠
Photo: Nike

Introducing Van Gogh’s Starry Night Limited Edition Flavor! 

When I got the call that we had the opportunity to the Portland Van Gogh/Monet art experience at the Oregon Convention Center, I quickly jumped at the chance. What is more beautiful than his Starry Night painting? So we got to work on how to deconstruct that painting into an ice cream and here’s what we came up with. Starry Night is a white maple cinnamon ice cream swirled with a rich blue vanilla ice cream to mimic Van Gogh’s brush strokes, studded with golden honeecomb “stars” and chocolate syrup drizzle to showcase the swirling sky and bright stars. It is available at all shops through February 1st. Make sure to grab tickets to the exhibit too!

🍌 Cottage Cheese Banana Bread Bites 🧁
These Cottage Cheese Banana Bread Bites are mini, protein-packed snacks that are perfect for breakfast on the go or a healthy treat. They’re soft, moist, and naturally sweetened with banana—deliciously satisfying and easy to make!
Ingredients
1 cup rolled oats
1/2 cup cottage cheese
1 large ripe banana, mashed
1 large egg
1/4 cup honey or maple syrup
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp cinnamon
**Pinch of salt
1/4 cup mini chocolate chips or chopped nuts (optional)
Directions
Step 1: Preheat Oven
Preheat Oven: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C) and lightly grease a mini muffin tin or line it with mini muffin liners.
Step 2: Prepare Batter
Blend Ingredients: In a blender or food processor, combine oats, cottage cheese, mashed banana, egg, honey or maple syrup, vanilla, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt. Blend until smooth.
Add Mix-Ins: Fold in chocolate chips or nuts if desired.
Step 3: Bake the Bites
Fill Muffin Tin: Pour the batter into the prepared mini muffin tin, filling each cup about 3/4 full.
Bake: Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center of a bite comes out clean.
Step 4: Cool and Serve
Cool Bites: Let the bites cool in the tin for a few minutes, then transfer them to a wire rack to cool completely.
Store: Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 5 days, or freeze for longer storage.
Nutritional Information
Calories: Approximately 80 calories per bite
Servings: Makes about 24 mini bites
Prep Time: 5 minutes
Cook Time: 12-15 minutes
Total Time: 17-20 minutes

People always say “you need to define what sets your business apart from all of the others” and, this is a huge part of it. 

Do we want our clients to make money from their investment?  100% yes, of course.  But, in this industry people have a tendency to get stuck on how much money a specific item is going to bring them in return, rather than looking at the bigger picture. 

The bigger picture, and the truth of the matter is this:
Yes, guests book for the amenities.  But what they REVIEW, and what they RETURN FOR, is the experience.  And the overall guest experience means nailing the details. 

We focus on the details, and by doing that the big picture comes together just right. 

It’s the whole thing together that is going to determine ROI, not just hot tub vs sauna or comforters vs. duvets (although the answer is almost always hot tub if you can’t do both, and duvets if your cleaners will agree to it 😅)

The thing is, Airbnb has started getting a bad name because of the hosts who focus too much on the dollars in their pocket and not enough on the service they are providing.  It’s part of a broader pattern of this in our society if you ask me.

ingredients:

- 2 oz freshly squeezed tangerine juice
- 1/2 oz lime juice
- 1/2 oz basil simple syrup (recipe below)
- thin slices of tangerine and a sprig of basil for garnish

basil simple syrup:
1. combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup water, and a handful of fresh basil leaves in a saucepan.
2. simmer over low heat until the sugar dissolves.
3. let steep for 10 minutes, then strain and cool.

method:
1. in a shaker filled with ice, combine tangerine juice, passion fruit purée, lime juice, and basil
simple syrup.
2. shake gently and strain into a tall glass filled with fresh ice.
3. top with passionfruit tangerine health-ade kombucha.
4. stir lightly and garnish with tangerine slices and a fresh basil sprig

Moist January: Everything in Moderation, Even Moderation.

A brisk winter evening, the wind bites at your skin, but you’re wrapped up in your coziest sweater, ready for something more intriguing than the usual whiskey or rum. Enter Calvados, the quiet rebel of cold-weather spirits. Born in Normandy, France, Calvados is distilled from apples (sometimes pears), carrying a sweet, fruity punch that makes every sip feel like a warm embrace for your taste buds.

This isn’t your everyday apple brandy—it’s the smooth, slightly spiced cousin that’s seen things, full of depth and complexity. It’s the drink that slides in when your usual bourbon or scotch starts feeling too predictable. Winter’s the perfect excuse to break out of your usual rotation, isn’t it? Whether you’re sipping it neat, shaking up a festive cocktail, or spiking your hot cider, Calvados delivers a cozy, layered experience few bottles can match.

Why add Calvados to your stash? Because it’s a chameleon—impressive at gatherings, comforting for a night by the fire, and just special enough to toast life’s small victories. Swing by LUSH, ask for our Calvados selection, and we’ll help you find the perfect bottle. Then head home, pour a glass, and let it transform a chilly evening into a taste of the Norman countryside. You’ll wonder how winter ever felt complete without it.

Moist January: Everything in Moderation, Even Moderation.

There are moments when the ordinary simply won’t do—when you long for something unexpected, something that lingers on the palate and in the memory. Enter escargot, that celebrated French delicacy, a little jewel of a dish, drenched in garlic, butter, and the kind of indulgence that whispers of far-off Parisian nights. After a recent sojourn in France, we at LUSH felt compelled to share this culinary treasure. Imagine, if you will, tender snails luxuriating in a butter infused with garlic, lemon, parsley, white wine, and just a hint of black pepper—a rich, comforting embrace that requires no passport, only a willingness to savor.

But perhaps snails are not your preference. No matter. For those who shy away from the thought of such creatures, we present the “escar-NO” option. Here, we substitute juicy chicken thighs, gently poached in that same sumptuous butter. The effect is nearly identical—a harmonious symphony of flavors, but with a more familiar, approachable centerpiece.

Whether you lean toward the adventurous or the traditional, your palate is in for a journey. Come to LUSH and let us whisk you away to the charm of a Parisian bistro, one buttery morsel at a time. We won’t pry into your choice; we’ll simply delight in your enjoyment. After all, fine dining, like fine living, is about the pleasure of the experience.

Indulge in succulent duck confit, layered with creamy raclette, peppery arugula, tangy mustard, zesty pickled onions, and crowned with crispy shallots – all nestled between a perfectly toasted baguette. It’s a symphony of flavors that’ll elevate your taste buds to new heights. Don’t miss out on this exquisite culinary experience, available now! 🌟

Hold onto your liver and brace yourself, because what we’ve got here at LUSH Roscoe Village is the wine world’s equivalent of stumbling onto buried treasure in the middle of a civilized desert. Domaine Rolly Gassmann—a mad genius of Alsace—has thrown open the vault, and we’re sitting on a lineup of vintages that’ll knock your senses sideways. These are not just bottles; these are legends in glass, and they date as far back as 2005. Here’s the twist of the cork: they’re priced so sensibly, you’d think we’d gone off our rockers. No velvet ropes, no nosebleed prices—just premium Alsace wine ready to leave you speechless.

And this collection? This is Rolly Gassmann’s finest—a kaleidoscope of vintages that could make even the most jaded wine critic weep. Every bottle is a deep dive into the best Alsace has to offer. These wines aren’t just for drinking—they’re for meditating over, for savoring with the kind of reverence usually reserved for epic poetry or rare jazz records. Drink it now, stash it for later, or both—these beauties have the staying power to shine for years.

So, don’t sit there dawdling—seize this opportunity before it slips away! Come bask in the genius of Rolly Gassmann, and let these wines haul you right to the stony, sun-soaked vineyards of Alsace. This, my friends, is as good as it gets.

Hold on to your buns, folks, because we’ve got something special sizzling in our kitchen perfect for a hot summer day, and ready to take the spot light - the LUSH Dog! 

This ain’t your average weiner, oh no. Picture this: an all-beef hot dog nestled in a garlic butter toasted brioche bun, adorned with gruyere, overnight onions, mustard, pickled onions, tomatoes, and a cornichon relish that’ll make your taste buds speechless. And let’s not forget the crispy fries on the side, because every superhero needs a trusty sidekick!

Whether you’re dining in or getting a platter to bring to a bbq or party, these dogs are sure to impress and be the star of the show.

Winter has finally made its grand entrance, draping everything in a snowy blanket. But inside the Roscoe Village dining room? It’s all warm, cozy vibes. Imagine yourself settling in with a drink by our imaginary fireplace—it’s just as comforting as the real thing, we promise.

While you’re here, you have to ask about the new Escar-No. Trust us, it’s a mystery worth solving, especially when paired with a crisp glass of Sancerre.

And hey, need a silver lining? Only 1,399 days until the next election. We’ve got this, one cozy, delicious day at a time.

Lush Wine & Spirits isn’t just about fine wines, craft cocktails, and a good time anymore—we’re now making waves in fashion! Introducing our 1st Edition T-Shirt, a bold way to take the Lush experience beyond the bottle.

This isn’t just merch; it’s a lifestyle. A statement. A way to share your refined-yet-relaxed outlook on life with the world. Slip into this exclusive tee for just $25 and show off your impeccable taste—not just in spirits, but in style.

Elevate your wardrobe with a shirt that’s as vibrant, fun, and timeless as your favorite glass of red—or white, or bubbly. For only $25, you can rep your favorite spot in town and look effortlessly chic doing it.

Our business development team is focused on identifying breakthrough science to help make a difference for patients. Hear more about our approach to collaborations. #JPM25
@merck discusses what they’re doing to help victims of the California wildfires.

We remain committed to advancing global health equity by supporting the development of stronger health systems that provide better and more equitable care. Learn more about how we work to expand access to health. 

#AccesstoHealth 
#HealthEquity

We’re at the forefront of research seeking to translate scientific discoveries into potential treatments for people with immune-mediated inflammatory disorders. This #CCAwarenessWeek, we are inspired by members of the IBD community, like Shonda, whose stories underscore the importance of this work.

Our pipeline has grown substantially, and so has our ability to leverage innovative analytical tools that power our drug discovery and development process. Watch how our Analytical R&D team plays a crucial role in driving this forward.
For more than 100 years, we’ve been advancing vaccines to help prevent a variety of potentially serious infectious diseases.

Our Analytical R&D team is at the core of drug discovery and development at Merck, partnering with cross-functional teams at every step of the way. Watch how they deliver critical data and insights to help overcome challenges and drive research forward.
Living with pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH) can be challenging, and Steve worried he wouldn’t be able to act again. See how reaching out for support helped him to keep doing what he loves most.

We continue to expand our R&D footprint with state-of-the-art research facilities to meet the needs of our evolving and increasingly more complex pipeline. Take a look inside our new Biologics Development Center at our Rahway, NJ headquarters where our scientists are driving forward new biologics research.
Leading-edge science requires creativity, tenacity and bold thinking. Watch our scientists debunk misconceptions about careers in STEM.

“It’s been a journey, but it’s been my journey.”

When Jill found herself diagnosed with HIV as a single mother of two small children, her world turned upside down. But she found strength through her faith and her family.

She and her young sons relied on each other, working together as a team. Now, she cherishes the tight-knit relationships she has with her grown-up sons. 

We’re proud to amplify voices like Jill’s on #WorldAIDSDay and every day through our #OwningMyHIVJourney series.

What is DSG Transmission?

DSG (Direct-Shift Gearbox) transmission is an advanced dual-clutch system designed to give you smoother, faster, and more efficient gear shifts. Unlike traditional automatic transmissions, DSG uses two clutches that pre-select the next gear, allowing for nearly instantaneous shifts without any loss of power. This results in a driving experience that’s not only more responsive but also more fuel-efficient. Whether you’re navigating city streets or cruising on the highway, DSG ensures you’re always in the right gear at the right time, delivering a seamless and exhilarating drive. With its lightning-fast shifts, DSG enhances both performance and comfort, making your driving experience truly enjoyable.

The following models have been offered either currently or in the past in the Indian market:

7-Speed DSG (DQ200): This version is often found in smaller, less powerful cars. It’s designed for maximum fuel efficiency and comfort, especially in city driving. Offered in cars like the Virtus, Polo, Vento etc.

6-Speed DSG (DQ250): This version is commonly used in more powerful cars and offers a balance of performance and efficiency. Offered in cars like the Jetta and the passat.

7-Speed Wet DSG (DQ381): Designed for high-performance vehicles with even greater power and torque. Like the 6-speed DSG, these also use wet clutches, ensuring durability and smooth operation even in more demanding driving conditions. Offered in cars like the Tiguan.

Experience the best of both worlds with DSG,
smooth, fast, and efficient gear shifts for a more enjoyable drive.

Overall, avocado oil is healthy — but it’s still a calorie-rich oil. Eating too much avocado or avocado oil can put you over your recommended calorie intake. Like any food, it’s best in moderation. 🥑 

The most distinctive quality of avocado oil, compared with olive oil, is its high smoke point. This means you can use it at higher temperatures before it burns. Try it next time you’re cooking with high heat, such as roasting, grilling or pan-frying. For the most health benefits, look for unrefined, cold-pressed avocado oil. Although avocado oil is very heat stable, processing may affect the levels of protective antioxidants.

We’re among the first hospitals in the U.S. to offer the FDA-approved tumor-infiltrating lymphocytes therapy for solid tumor cancer. The treatment amplifies immune cells in a patient’s tumor and enhances their ability to fight the cancer. It’s the first cellular therapy for patients with unresectable or metastatic melanoma who haven’t responded to other treatments.
 
Here’s how it works. Tumor-infiltrating lymphocytes or TIL therapy leverages the body’s own T lymphocytes that are in contact with a harvested tumor site to seek out and destroy other tumors cells and targets. TIL cells recognize and attack tumor cells. However, it requires many of these cells to do the job. The goal is to make enough cells for the therapy to succeed.
 
The process begins with a surgeon removing a melanoma tumor from the patient. Immune cells from the tumor are then isolated and extracted in a lab and made into an infusion later sent to the patient’s care team. After this process, the patient receives a lymphodepleting chemotherapy regimen to prepare their body to accept the TIL cells that will be infused. Within 24 hours of the lymphodepleting chemotherapy, the generated TIL cells are infused back into the patient, where they then work to find and destroy the melanoma tumor cells.
 
When the FDA granted accelerated approval of TIL treatment with lifileucel for patients with metastatic melanoma, we were one of 23 select Early-Authorized Treatment Centers across the country approved to administer this new form of cellular therapy.
 
Trials are underway for TIL therapy in patients with other cancers as well as studies of other TIL products. Researchers believe this treatment approach is likely to benefit patients with a wide range of solid tumors.

Pneumonia is an infection in your lungs caused by bacteria, viruses or fungi. Pneumonia causes your lung tissue to swell (inflammation) and can cause fluid or pus in your lungs. It makes it difficult to breathe and can cause a fever and cough with yellow, green or bloody mucus. Bacterial pneumonia is usually more severe than viral pneumonia, which often resolves on its own.⁣
⁣
Pneumonia can affect one or both lungs. Pneumonia in both of your lungs is called bilateral or double pneumonia. Treatment depends on the cause and severity of pneumonia.

Not all coughing is a sign of heart failure. There’s a host of reasons you may have a cough. Irritants or allergens like smoke, mold, dust and pollen can cause you to cough. Certain medical conditions like a cold, flu, pneumonia, acid reflux and sinusitis can also make you cough. But if you’re experiencing heart cough symptoms or have been diagnosed with asthma or bronchitis and your cough doesn’t improve with treatment, you should talk to your doctor about heart failure.

When you have that unpleasant feeling in your throat, it’s hard to know what the exact cause is. Acid reflux, heartburn and GERD are terms often used together, but they’re not the same thing. But they sometimes come as a package deal.

Have you gotten your flu shot yet? 💉 If you’re someone with specific food allergies, like an allergy to eggs, you may have been told in the past not to get the influenza vaccine. Why? The flu vaccine contains a small amount of egg protein, so people with egg allergies were once advised to avoid it. But keep in mind that your risk of getting the flu outweigh your risk of an allergic reaction to the egg protein in the vaccine.

We have updated findings from our preventative breast cancer vaccine study aimed at preventing triple-negative breast cancer.
We found it was generally well tolerated and produced an immune response in most patients.
The team described the side effects of the vaccine, showed the highest tolerated dose to date, and presented the immunologic effects of the vaccine. Findings are being presented at the Society for Immunotherapy of Cancer Annual Meeting.
Launched in 2021 and funded by the U.S. Department of Defense, the ongoing clinical trial is evaluating safety and monitoring immune response of the vaccine. The phase 1 study, conducted at Cleveland Clinic’s main campus in partnership with Anixa Biosciences, Inc., has included 26 patients to date.
Anixa is planning a phase 2 study to evaluate the efficacy of the vaccine. The trial is expected to begin in 2025 and is projected to last approximately two to three years.

After working on her graduate school application from a hospital ICU bed, 25-year-old Molly Easly went on to get her bachelor’s and master’s degrees at the same time. Her resilience made this accomplishment possible even amid an aortic dissection and cancer diagnosis.⁣
⁣
Ever since she was young, Molly’s heart was monitored because of her family history of aortic dissections. “When I initially evaluated Molly, her above average size aorta with her family history was a marker even before we had the benefit of positive genetic testing,” says pediatric cardiologist Dr. Kenneth Zahka, who adds testing later confirmed Molly has an ACTA2 mutation, which increases a person’s risk of aortic aneurysms and dissections.⁣
⁣
After finding an abrupt increase in the size of her aorta, Dr. Zahka referred her to cardiothoracic surgeon Dr. Eric Roselli, who decided to move forward with surgery to address her dilated aorta. “We were able to save Molly’s valve while replacing her root and ascending aorta to prevent her from having what we call a Type A dissection, which is a serious, life-threatening emergency. We also replaced her arch to prepare for later potential aortic problems,” says Dr. Roselli.⁣
⁣
From there, Molly was regularly monitored for any changes with her aorta. She thought everything was back to normal up until a little over three years after her first surgery when she had a Type B dissection, which is typically less dangerous than a Type A dissection. “Because I did that more extended repair a few years prior, we were able to better control her condition in the intensive care unit and then get her treated with a minimally invasive operation,” says Dr. Roselli.⁣
⁣
While addressing the dissection, Molly’s care team spotted a nodule on her thyroid, which testing confirmed was thyroid cancer. Amid juggling doctor’s appointments, Molly managed to graduate college and currently has no evidence of cancer after treatment. She credits her care team with saving her life and being able to go on to meet her husband, Briggs Krause, who Molly learned is also a patient of Dr. Zahka’s. In October 2024, Molly and Briggs said, “I do.”

🔥My 60K Success List👇

🥂If you want to build your 7 Figure Audience Empire on Instagram so you effortlessly attract clients & customers on repeat, comment “EMPIRE”

Yes there was strategy, & I had some luck.

But, if you want to make yourself lucky, you have to put yourself out there more. You CAN do this 🙌

The DOs - What I did:

✅ Focused almost exclusively on reels - they have incredible organic reach right now
✅ Posted 2 reels a day - yes, this is crazy for some people, but I learned quickly, & had fast Instagram growth
✅ Talked about my results from my business to build credibility
✅ Gave detailed captions, like this, to give MAX value to viewers, and to build trust & connection
✅ Used phrases to cheer on my community
✅ Leveraged emotion in my text on screen
✅ Planned my hooks
✅ Focused making content that helped my audience with their top goals & the results they wanted
✅ Used a combination of long & short reels
✅ Made sure to use my voice in at least 25% of my reels
✅ Used almost exclusively trending sounds with 10K views or less, but strategically
✅ Chose sounds that best matched the vibe/mood of my message & my clip
✅ Used keywords in my captions
✅ Asked people to take action, like follow, save, share & comment a specific word
✅ Took B-roll everyday (non-speaking clips of me doing daily tasks, & out and about)

Wooo if you got this far! Let’s keep going…

Remember to save this 👉💾

The DON’TS - What I didn’t do:

❌ Paid for promotion or engagement
❌ Paid for shoutouts
❌ Did a giveaway
❌ Posted at a specific time - I posted when my reels were done
❌ Stress about hashtags - I just did my best to choose hashtags related to my audience
❌ Expected immediate results - it took a while before any of my reels went past 250 views
❌ Just slapped trending sounds on a reel and expected it to “go viral” because the audio was trending
❌ Spent hours filming beautiful clips - I used simple B-roll instead

🥂If you want to build your 7 Figure Audience Empire on Instagram so you effortlessly attract clients & customers on repeat, comment “EMPIRE”

(🎉We’re celebrating 8.7M+ followers gained for my students)

🤯My 40K in 30 days journey👇

Yes, I had a strategy, but No I didn’t know it would turn out like THIS…

💾 Remember to save this and ❤️follow so you can grow on Instagram too!

Let’s get you growing!

REELS: I posted 2 reels a day. Yep it’s a lot, but I wanted fast Instagram growth and I’m in a sprint.

RESEARCH: I researched up my audience’s top goals, problems, and questions and made my reels about those.

(This is also how I built a following of 270K on TikTok and helped my students hit 3.8M followers and over 1B views.)

PATH: I looked for proven reel formulas (one that went viral) or a from successful creator in my niche to model. Then I put my own spin on the reel.

HOOKS: Right now I’m using strong text hooks that use curiosity, are specific, highlight a pain point, problem or a result they want. These work! 

LUCK & STRATEGY: I saw another creator go viral with a remix… So I remixed the same video, and mine went viral too.🤯

SOUNDS: I chose small trending sounds, usually under 10K. For text on screen videos, I tried to make them loop and go to the caption.

COMMENTS: I focussed on comments instead of likes, and responded with a question to boost the engagement and connection further ❤️

VALUE BOMBS: Every video I tried to give as much value as possible. I asked myself: What would make them want to save or hit follow?

TEXT ON SCREEN TO CAPTION: I spend time writing a value-rich caption because the reel loops in the background getting more views and I gain credibility with the details I add here.

SERIES: One of the best helpers for Instagram growth was making a series and repeating best types of videos! 

TAKE ACTION: I asked people to take action in as many places as possible: Verbally & in the caption in multiple places for people to:

🔥My Secret to BOOST Engagement on Reels⬇️

This strategy is how I went from hitting 100s of views on my reels, to hitting 10,000s a few weeks later (13M accounts reached in 30 days 🤯).

They’re also the same strategies I teach to my students and clients. 

📣 Comment “EMPIRE” if you’re ready to grow your own 7 Figure Audience Empire on IG.

1. HOT topic: What are the hot topics in your niche?

⚡️Look for your best performing videos – what are those topics?
⚡️Look at another creators in your niche – what are their best performing videos about?
⚡️Look at the comments and questions on your posts, and the posts of your competitors – what are people talking about?

2. Sticky Hooks!

If we can’t make people stop in the first 1 - 2 seconds of your reel, they won’t stay to watch… and this causes low views.

So… make sure your hook includes the problem you solve, the result, the benefit or goal your audience wants OR something that makes people curious.

3. Strategic calls to action

Want to know one of my best secrets for getting my content out to more people?

I ask people to engage! But how does it work?

🫶I remind people to share my content - If this was helpful, share it with a friend!

This helps me build a community and reach new people, everyday. And it can help you too :).

🔥My 3 Non-Negotiables for HIGH Reach👇

It’s been really fun watching my students use these to explode their reach!

🔥 Reels need a boost in views? 👉Comment “57” for my free Viral Hooks Cheat Sheet

(My students just passed 8.7M followers in growth)

1. Multi-Dimensional Intro:
Capturing attention on Instagram in the first 2 seconds in non-negotiable for high reach.

If you want to give yourself the best chance to grab those potential followers’ eyeballs, you want to use more than one strategy.

Here I used a visual hook (running away from the screen & a photo). I also used text on screen with a question. And I used music that made it sounds like something was going to “happen”.

All of this grabs attention & makes people want to watch. It’s probably why you’re here now 👋😊.

👉Comment “57” to get my free Viral Hooks Cheat Sheet

2. The Nugget:
This is the heart of your reel. And we don’t want to guess about this if you want to increase your reach.

It’s time to do some research. What are your audience’s top problems, goals or questions?

I didn’t guess for this reel. I know that one of my audience’s biggest problems is low reach.

And, I made sure my hook was exactly what my audience is asking - or typing into Google.

3. Rewatch:
What’s one of the best ways to boost your reach on Instagram? Keep people watching for longer.

The longer people watch your reel, the greater the signal to Instagram that your content is worth pushing to more people.

So, you can get people to read your caption, or you can also make something interesting happen on screen so people want to re-watch.

In my reel, I made words pop up on my claps, & I kicked text onto the screen.

A lot of people will watch the reel again because it was interesting, then they’ll go to the caption to read.

We urge you to practice Anulom Vilom in our 21-Day Yoga Sadhana Beginner Program. The link is in our Bio. 🧘

Anulom Vilom is an effective Pranayama that brings movement to our Prana/energy body. 🌬️

There are many energy channels (also called Nadis) in our body. 2 main nadis are known as Ida and Pingala nadis. 🌀

According to ancient scriptures, Ida and Pingala are along the spinal cord. 📜

While Ida is associated with the left nostril, Pingala connects to the right nostril. 👃

If your left nostril is open, you are calm and relaxed. ⬅️

An open right nostril signifies active, energetic, and in action. ➡️

When you are stressed, Pingala nadi is working in excess. It is also the same when you feel burnt out or overworking your body. 🤯

To find balance, smoothen down, and bring back calmness, practice anulom vilom. 😌

Anulom Vilom helps to equalize our state of relaxation and activeness. ✨
.
.
.
.

If you wish to open the door of self-punishment, you use the key of ‘guilt’. 

If you wish to open the doors of blame and complaints, you use the key of ‘resentment’.

These two emotions put you in a whirlpool of self-torture. And, you sit in these turbulences alone. 🌪️

You were not born to live in mediocrity, sadness, and anger. You are a witness of life, here to enjoy all the good things of this world. ☀️

So, gather the courage to look at yourself in the mirror. Love and appreciate each part of you, even the broken ones. 🥰

Learn from the decisions you made when you did not know better. Take the resolve to make yourself proud with each new choice. By forgiving yourself, you create your path to freedom. 🍃

Release hold of the anger you have for others. It does not matter who was right or wrong because, right now, you are burning alone in this rage. Your aim is not to prove yourself but to live your life fully. ❤️

Once you let go of these emotions, do not look back. Choose your peace over anything that causes you harm. 🙏
.
.
.
.

「これなんだと思う？」「フライドポテトじゃないよ！」おどろきの新食感♪フライドなす / Fried Eggplant
@tastyjapan 👈他のレシピもチェック！

1人分

材料：
なす　1本
【A】コーンスターチ　大さじ2　
【A】片栗粉　大さじ2
揚げ油　適量

作り方：
① なすはヘタを残して皮をむき、縦に4〜5等分に切り込みを入れる。さらに切り込みが入ってない面を上にして、3〜4等分に切り込みを入れ、ほうきのような形にする。
② 【A】を混ぜ合わせ、①にまぶす。
③ 揚げ物用の鍋に底から5センチほど揚げ油を注ぎ、170度に熱する 。②を静かに入れて、両面がきつね色になるまで揚げたら、完成！ 

お好みで塩をふったり、トマトケチャップをつけたりして召し上がれ♪

===

Fried Eggplant
Servings: 1
 
INGREDIENTS
1 eggplant
 
A
 2 tablespoons corn starch
 2 tablespoons potato starch
 
Frying oil, as needed
 
PREPARATION
1. Peel the eggplant with the stem kept on. Cut as shown in the video to make it like a broom.
2. Mix the ingredients A and dust the eggplant (1) with them.
3. Pour the oil to cover 5cm of a frying pot. Heat to 170°C/ 338°F. Put (2) in the oil and cook until golden.
4. Enjoy with salt or tomato ketchup as you like♪

【豆腐料理で身体も心もポカポカ温まろう〜！！】腸活レシピ Collaboration With DAIGOも台所 / Tofu with Dashi Sauce 
@tastyjapan 👈他のレシピもチェック！

2人分

材料：
豆腐（絹）　1丁（250g）
白菜　200g
ちくわ　2本
しいたけ　3枚
しょうが　10g
青ネギ　1本
【☆煮汁】
【A】だし　500ml
【A】みりん　大さじ2
【A】薄口しょうゆ　大さじ1/3
【A】塩　小さじ1/3
水溶き片栗粉　適量

作り方：　
① 豆腐はペーパータオルに挟んで10分おく。
② 白菜の軸は7ミリ幅、4センチの長さに切り、葉は4センチ角に切る。ちくわは3ミリ幅の輪切りにし、しいたけは5ミリ幅に切り、しょうがは千切り、青ネギは小口切りにする。
③ フライパンに【A】を入れて強火で煮立て、しょうが、白菜、ちくわ、しいたけを加えて中火で7分煮る。
④ 豆腐は半分に切って一口大に切り、③に加えてサッと煮る。
⑤ ④に水溶き片栗粉を加えて豆腐を崩さないようにとろみをつける。器に盛って、青ネギをのせたら、完成！

===

Tofu with Dashi Sauce
Servings: 2

INGREDIENTS
1 (250g) tofu (silken)
200g Chinese cabbage
2 chikuwa
3 shiitake mushrooms
10g ginger
1 string scallion
[Dashi Sauce]
A
500ml dashi broth
2 tablespoons mirin
1/3 tablespoon soy sauce
1/3 teaspoon salt
Potato starch with water, as needed

PREPARATION
1. Wrap the tofu with paper towels and leave for 10 minutes.
2. Cut the green part of the Chinese cabbage into 4cm pieces, and shreds the white part into small pieces (7mm x 4cm). Cut the chikuwa into 3mm slices. Cut the shiitake mushrooms into 5mm slices. Shredded the ginger. Chop the scallion.
3. Heat all of the ingredients A in a pan on high heat. Add the ginger, the Chinese cabbage, the chikuwa, and the shiitake mushrooms. Simmer for 7 minutes on medium heat.
4. Cut the tofu into bite-sized pieces and add to the pan.
5. Add the potato starch (mixed with water) into the pan. Simmer to thicken. Transfer to a bowl. Add chopped scallions on top.
6. Enjoy!

#tastyjapan #豆腐の煮もの #豆腐 # DAIGOも台所

【えびの旨みがギュッ♡】ほっこりおうちごはん♡白菜たっぷりぷりぷり水ギョーザにハマる！ / Dumplings with Chinese Cabbage Fillings
@tastyjapan 👈他のレシピもチェック！

2人分

材料：
ギョーザの皮　14枚
むきえび　70g
白菜　1枚（100g）
塩　小さじ1/2
【A】片栗粉　大さじ1
【A】鶏がらスープの素　小さじ1
【A】酒　小さじ1/2
【A】ごま油　小さじ1/2
水 適量
【B】酢　大さじ1
【B】しょうゆ　大さじ1
輪切り唐辛子　適量
小ネギ（小口切り）　適量

作り方：
① むきえびはキッチンペーパーで水分を拭き取り、粗みじん切りにする。白菜はみじん切りにして塩を加え、塩もみする。しんなりしたら水分を絞る。
② ボウルに①と【A】を入れて混ぜる。
③ ギョーザの皮に②をおき、縁に水を塗ったら半分にたたみ両端をつける。
④ 沸騰したお湯に③を入れ、浮いてくるまで5分ほどゆでる。
⑤ 器に盛り、混ぜた【B】をかける。輪切り唐辛子と小口切りにした小ネギをのせたら、完成！

===

Dumplings with Chinese Cabbage Fillings
Servings: 2

INGREDIENTS
12 dumpling wrappers
70g shrimp (peeled and deveined)
1 leaf (100g) Chinese cabbage
1/2 teaspoon salt
A
 1 tablespoon potato starch
 1 teaspoon chicken stock powder
 1/2 teaspoon sake
 1/2 teaspoon sesame oil
Water, as needed
B
 1 tablespoon vinegar
 1 tablespoon soy sauce
Chopped chili, as needed
Chopped scallions, as needed

PREPARATION
1. Pat dry shrimp with paper towels and then chop. Shred the Chinese cabbage and rub with salt. When the cabbage is soften, squeeze the liquid out. 
2. Mix all of the ingredients A with (1) in a bowl. 
3. Place some of (2) in the center of a dumpling wrapper. Wet the edges of the wrapper and fold in to close.
4. Bring a pot of water to a boil. Boil (3) for about 5 minutes.
5. Place the dumplings on a plate. Pour the sauce (B). Put some chopped chili and chopped scallions on top.
6. Enjoy!

【お寿司が秒で握れる？！】「夢みたいな裏技だ♡」お家で簡単！本格寿司のレシピ / Ultimate Sushi Hack
@tastyjapan 👈他のレシピもチェック！

1人分

材料：
ご飯　200g
粉末すし酢　大さじ1
お好きな具材　10個

作り方：
① 温かいごはんに粉末すし酢を混ぜて、うちわで仰ぎながら冷ます。
② 水でぬらしたまな板の上に、型枠を置き、①を詰め、押し型で軽く押して形を整える。
③ ②の上に具材を並べる。
④ ③を押し型の上にのせ、押し込んで型から取り出したら、完成！

===

Ultimate Sushi Hack
Servings: 1

INGREDIENTS
200g steamed rice
1 tablespoon sushi vinegar powder
10 pieces your favorite sushi toppings

PREPARATION

What if your flopped posts could be transformed into viral content with this simple tweak? 
Hooks are still very important in 2025! But, as you may have noticed…What used to work, is falling flat!

The truth is, if you want to succeed on Instagram (or any social media platform) — you have to get used to things changing!🫣

You have to be okay with switching up your content, your strategy, & your messaging every so often!

Not because “the algorithm changed”…(although yes, this might be true)! But, it only changes b/c—

WE CHANGE! How we consume content changes! 

So, in order to continue to reach new people & grow your following with an engaged audience, you have to be willing to change!👏

Now, then”old hooks” still work — but they are not nearly as strong as they used to be! If you’re serious about hitting your Instagram goals in 2025, you might want to switch things up a bit!

There are so many different types of hooks that work well! And which type you use will differ based on a multitude of factors! But, the “Empowered & Emotional Hook” is crushing it right now!

Here are some examples: 
❌Old hook: How to stay motivated for the gym
✔️Improved hook: Turn workouts you dread into a routine you love with lasting results you’re proud of!  
❌Old hook: The best nighttime routine for busy parents ✔️Improved hook: Imagine putting an end to that chaotic bedtime routine and feeling calm and connected with your child every night!
 ❌Old hook: 10 Tips For More Energy
✔️Improved hook: How to turn your sleepless nights into energized mornings without coffee!  ❌Old hook: Date night idea for struggling couples
✔️Improved hook: If you feel like your relationship has lost its spark, steal this date night idea to reignite the flame!
