Did you know the ORIGINAL @theescapegame is in Berry Hill? And, did you know they have a 5 star google rating with over 10,000 (!!!) reviews? 

This was my first time at the Escape Game, and only my second time doing an escape room ever - and I can see why this particular site is so beloved. The puzzles were well thought out, the staff was kind and appropriately helpful, and everything seemed clean and organized. 

This is the perfect summer activity when the big kids are starting to get restless (best for ages 13 and up) or for when family is visiting and you need something the whole group can do. They also have late night games if you want to extend a date night! 

I definitely recommend the Special Ops room we did, but there are all kinds of scenarios at varying skill levels, so choose one that best suits you. And, if downtown or Opry Mills is more convenient, those locations have 5 stars, too!

If you’ve never done an escape room, if you’ve never been to @theescapegame, or if it’s just been too long, this is your sign to check it out. We had a blast and know you will, too.

If you’re a puzzle enthusiast who enjoys solving clues, then you simply must try @theescapegame in Santa Clara. We recently tried one of their rooms called “The Depths,” where the objective is to uncover the secrets of a submerged lab. The room is incredibly immersive, with plenty of interactive elements to keep you engaged. The puzzles are ingeniously designed and quite challenging, so if you’re tackling it as a group, it’s crucial to delegate responsibilities effectively. With only sixty minutes on the clock, every second counts, so be sure to manage your time wisely. As for our experience, we were down to the wire and almost didn’t make it, but we rallied together and successfully escaped! Do you have what it takes to escape this room?

Unique and fun adventure alert! 🚨 Imagine finding a fun family outing that ages 7 to 45 can enjoy together 👏 #sponsored

Come along with my kids, my niece and nephews as the eight of us visit The Escape Game on the Country Club Plaza. Spoiler alert, we escaped (barely) and are already making plans to go back and try another room with new challenges!

My kids have done several escape room challenges before for friends’ birthday parties and they were incredibly excited to bring their cousins along. This was my first time doing an escape room and I had no idea what to expect or how it would go with such a big age range but it was fun from start to finish.

From the moment our one hour adventure began @theescapegame it was a high-energy, team oriented feeling as we worked together to figure out clues and codes to unlock new rooms and escape with one minute to spare. I loved that we could ask for hints when we got stuck and it was a fabulous way to bond and connect as a family.

The staff was very welcoming, kind and had a great energy! We chose the easiest room, “Timeliner: Train Through Time”, which was perfect for our group. The team was great about making that recommendation based upon our kids’ ages and this being the first escape room for several in our group. I liked that they have a range of themes and skill levels. We also loved the location so we could grab lunch at The Cheesecake Factory on The Country Club Plaza after we escaped.

I’m also saving this as a gift idea for hard to shop for kids, teens and tweens for birthdays and holidays. 

Have you tried The Escape Game? Were you surprised to learn it was fun for all ages?

::Newsflash:: 
I LOVE PICKLES!!!
🥒🥒🥒🥒🥒🥒🥒
and I finally tried Burger King's PICKLE FRIES today as my afternoon snack (with a meal...lol)

1) the pickles used are like Klausen pickles...white pickle meat. A little silly with the spices

2) I think the batter is the same as the nugget batter, I got a lil black pepper taste with it that I liked a lot and the batter wasn't too thin. Good crust

3) I got ketchup but the ranch that came with it was very complementary to my taste buds 

My verdict???
 
A good thing was done here! 🤤

I'll give it 8 out of 10 stars
⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐__ __

-🥴 only because for $3.99 I would rather get a medium sized portion of pickle fries and not the kiddie small 

#hack 
if you get a meal, you can sub the regular fries for pickle fries for $1.50 +1⭐

Has anyone else tried these yet??

Hormonal health > Willpower. Always.
And Oprah is right: fit healthy people don’t think about food all day. We eat when you’re hungry and stop when starting to feel full (never past that point).

For years, I thought my constant hunger, cravings, and obsession with food meant I just wasn’t “disciplined” enough. I blamed myself for not being able to stick to diets or resist temptation. But here’s the truth: it was never about willpower.

When your hormones are out of balance, no amount of willpower can overcome the chaos happening inside your body.

Here’s what I’ve learned:

💚 GLP-1, a hormone from your gut, keeps blood sugar stable, slows digestion, and helps you feel satisfied after meals.
💚 Leptin (the “fullness” hormone) and ghrelin (the “hunger” hormone) work together to regulate appetite—but they depend on other hormones to stay balanced.
💚 Estrogen boosts GLP-1, enhances leptin sensitivity, and helps suppress ghrelin (reducing unnecessary hunger).
💚 Progesterone influences these signals, especially during the luteal phase, when it can increase ghrelin and cravings if out of balance.
💚 Cortisol disrupts this entire system when it’s too high, spiking ghrelin and blocking leptin, making you feel hungrier than you really are.

When GLP-1, leptin, and ghrelin are supported by balanced estrogen, progesterone, and cortisol, hunger and cravings feel effortless. You eat when you’re hungry, stop when you’re full, and don’t need to rely on willpower to control your choices.

The winter itch isn't just in your head - there's solid science behind why our skin becomes more irritated during colder months. When temperatures drop and indoor heating kicks in, our skin faces a perfect storm of conditions that trigger itching. 🥶

The primary culprit is low humidity. Cold winter air holds less moisture than warm air, and indoor heating further strips the remaining humidity from our environment. Our skin responds by losing water more rapidly through a process called transepidermal water loss. This compromises our skin barrier - the protective outer layer that keeps moisture in and irritants out.

A compromised skin barrier sets off a chain reaction. The dry, damaged barrier activates nerve endings, which send itch signals to our brain. 🧠

Additionally, when skin becomes too dry, it releases inflammatory compounds that amplify the itch sensation. This explains why scratching provides temporary relief but ultimately makes things worse by further damaging the barrier.

For people with eczema (atopic dermatitis), winter presents additional challenges. Their skin already has a weakened barrier function due to genetic factors affecting certain proteins. The harsh winter conditions exacerbate this vulnerability, leading to more frequent and severe flare-ups.

THE SOLUTION LIES IN SUPPORTING OUR SKIN BARRIER:
👉Using thick moisturizers immediately after bathing to trap water in the skin
👉Installing humidifiers to maintain indoor moisture levels
👉Taking shorter, lukewarm showers instead of hot baths
👉Wearing soft, breathable fabrics that don't irritate the skin. 

Understanding this science helps explain why simply scratching isn't the answer. Instead, focusing on barrier repair and humidity management can provide lasting relief from winter's persistent itch. ❄️

The Skin-Gut-Brain-Biome “Axis” is believed to explain correlations among the gut microbiota, emotional states, and systemic skin inflammation. 

Many skin disorders are now thought to originate in the gut microbiome.  Disturbances in mucosal lining, microbiome dysbiosis, overgrowth of bacteria in small intestines, can all appear as rashes, flares, or even the onset of skin diseases such as acne, eczema, or psoriasis. 

Imbalance of the intestinal microbiome can cause excess bacterial growth of pathobionts, leading to competition for nutrients and toxic metabolite production. This results in local and systemic inflammation affecting the physiology of the skin. Maintaining the integrity of tight junctions and the permeability of intestinal epithelial cells is crucial.

There is a link between the gut microbiome and eczema, and some research suggests that changes to the gut microbiome may be a factor in the development of eczema.  This imbalance may contribute to the inflammation and immune responses that are implicated in eczema.

A study found that the gut microbiome of infants with eczema differed from that of healthy infants. The study found that pathogenic species such as Escherichia, Shigella or Clostridium were more abundant in infants with eczema, while the species Bifidobacterium was more abundant in healthy infants [1].

Eating a plant-based, anti-inflammatory diet may help some people with eczema. Eating fermented foods while pregnant may reduce the risk of a child developing eczema [2].

References:
1.	https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5094743/

Did you know that 50% of Florida drivers do not meet the legally mandated minimum car insurance coverage in Florida? And 27% drive without any insurance at all.

Watch Attorney Ethan break down Florida auto insurance limits, then read the recap below to review which policies are required and available to all Florida drivers.

1️⃣ Property Damage Liability (PDL) - required
PDL covers damage to others' property, but not your own vehicle. Florida requires a minimum of $10,000 PDL coverage.

2️⃣ Personal Injury Protection (PIP) - required
Florida law mandates PIP, covering 80% of medical expenses up to $10,000 from a covered injury, regardless of fault. PIP also provides $5,000 in death benefits for fatalities.

3️⃣ Bodily Injury Liability (BIL) - elective for most (required for some*)
BIL safeguards others if you're at fault in a severe accident. While not mandatory for most, it's recommended. BIL covers medical costs, legal fees, loss of income, pain and suffering, and more.

*BIL is required for drivers with a DUI conviction within 3 years.

4️⃣ Uninsured & Underinsured Motorist Coverage - elective
UM/UIM protects you from at-fault drivers with no bodily liability insurance. UM also kicks in if you exceed your PIP coverage. 

5️⃣ Collision Coverage - elective
Collision insurance pays for vehicle damage from accidents, regardless of fault. It covers repairs when the other driver has insufficient or no insurance.

6️⃣ Comprehensive Coverage - elective
Comprehensive auto insurance coverage is designed to cover damage to your vehicle that is not caused by a crash with another vehicle. For example, a cracked windshield as a result of flying debris.

7️⃣ Medical Payment - elective
MedPay covers medical expenses up to your policy's limit, supplementing PIP.

Florida's required car insurance minimums might not offer the protection you need. We strongly advise drivers to seek insurance above these mandated levels.

The strength of your accident claim lies in the evidence you gather.🛡️ From documenting the scene to obtaining medical evaluations, every piece of evidence plays a vital role in securing the compensation you deserve. 

Avoid these common mistakes that can weaken your case:

1️⃣ Forgetting to get other driver's information
Gather crucial details from the other driver, including their name, contact information, and insurance policy number so your attorney can contact them later.

2️⃣ Skipping medical evaluation
Car accident victims who skip getting a medical evaluation can hurt their claim. This evidence can be used by an attorney to strengthen your case. 

3️⃣ Not collecting evidence
Take photos of your vehicle, the other driver's vehicle, any injuries you may have, and any other proof that contributed to the accident. 

4️⃣ Filing for insurance ASAP
Filing for insurance too soon can hurt your case since you may lack evidence or proof that you were the victim. While prompt action is essential, it shouldn't be rushed.

5️⃣ Admitting fault
Rushing to report can lead to accidental admissions of fault. Avoid speaking to your insurance adjuster without consulting an attorney first.

6️⃣ Delaying legal help
Don't make the mistake of waiting to contact an attorney until you run into issues with the insurance adjuster. The best way to prevent this is to contact a car accident lawyer before talking to your insurance. 

7️⃣ Talking to other driver's insurance reps
Steer clear of conversations with the other driver's insurance. Their aim is to minimize their client's responsibility.

8️⃣ Settling too early
Handling your claim independently can lead to early settlements, potentially shortchanging your compensation. An attorney can help you determine a fair offer and what you need in your situation.

🚨 New Law in Florida: Online Protection for Minors

Beginning January 1, 2025, Florida’s HB 3 introduces stricter online regulations to shield children from potential social media and online harms:

✔️ No social media accounts for children under 14.
✔️ Parental consent required for 14-15-year-olds to create accounts.
✔️ Websites with explicit content must use age verification to block minors.

Under the new law, social media platforms are required to terminate accounts belonging to minors under 14 or minors aged 14-15 who do not have parental consent. Parents or guardians can also request account termination.

Social media platforms are regulated under the bill if they:
🚩 Allow users to upload content or view the content or activity of other users.
🚩 Satisfy certain daily active user metrics identified in the bill.
���� Employ algorithms that analyze user data to select content for users.
🚩 Have certain addictive features.

Violations by platforms or websites could result in hefty penalties under the Florida Deceptive and Unfair Trade Practices Act.

Gov. Ron DeSantis stated, “HB 3 gives parents a greater ability to protect their children.” The law aims to safeguard minors from harmful online environments and ensure parental oversight for younger teens navigating social media.

#floridalaw #onlineprotection #socialmediaregulations #digitalparenting #stayinformed #HB3 #protectingminors #socialmedia

🚨 New Law in Florida: Protecting First Responders 

As of January 1, 2025, a new law (SB 184) makes it a second-degree misdemeanor to:

➡️ Interfere with a first responder’s ability to perform their duties.
➡️ Threaten a first responder with physical harm.
➡️ Harass a first responder.

This includes staying 25 feet away after a verbal warning not to approach. Violating this law can result in up to 60 days in jail.

The bill defines “first responder” as a law enforcement officer, correctional probation officer, firefighter, or an emergency medical care provider. First responders put their lives on the line every day to keep us safe. Let’s show them the respect they deserve and avoid actions that could harm them or disrupt their work.

Stay informed. Stay respectful.

- Welcome to#trippinwithtarte Necker Island 💜 While we planned & booked this trip a year ago to celebrate 10 years of #trippinwithtarte, we recognize the timing is challenging. Our hearts are with everyone impacted by the devastating wildfires. 

Giving back has always been a cornerstone of our trips & this one is no exception—we’re committed to supporting those impacted in meaningful ways. This trip is all about rest, recharge & connection. From Pilates to sound baths & more, we’re embracing time together on this sustainability-focused island💜

Meet the wild side of Necker Island 🦜🐢 This paradise is a sanctuary for some incredible wildlife. From lemurs to flamingos, the island is home to conservation efforts that protect & nurture endangered species 🌴❤️🐒 #tarteisland #shapetapeisland #trippinwithtarte

Our hearts are with everyone affected by the devastating wildfires in California. 💜

टीम इंडिया के पूर्व ओपनर वीरेंद्र सहवाग को लेकर एक चौंकाने वाली खबर सामने आई है. कुछ रिपोर्ट्स में ऐसा दावा किया गया है कि वीरेंद्र सहवाग और उनकी पत्नी आरती अहलावत 20 साल की शादी के बाद अलग हो रहे हैं. जानकारी के मुताबिक इस कपल ने इंस्टाग्राम पर एक-दूसरे को अनफॉलो भी कर दिया है, जिससे बाद उनके रिश्ते में दरार की अटकलें लगाई जा रही हैं. बता दें कि अप्रैल 2004 में वीरेंद्र सहवाग और आरती अहलावत की शादी हुई थी. अब उनकी शादी को लगभग 21 साल हो चुके हैं. आरती और वीरेंद्र सहवाग दो बच्चों आर्यवीर और वेदांत के माता-पिता हैं. मीडिया रिपोर्ट्स के मुताबिक परिवार के करीबी सूत्रों का कहना है कि वीरेंद्र सहवाग और उनकी पत्नी आरती अहलावत दोनों कई महीनों से अलग रह रहे हैं और तलाक की संभावना है. इस कपल के दो बच्चे आर्यवीर और वेदांत हैं. आर्यवीर का जन्म साल 2007 में हुआ था. वहीं, वेदांत का जन्म साल 2010 में हुआ था. कुछ महीनों पहले एक दिवाली समारोह के दौरान वीरेंद्र सहवाग ने अपने बेटों और परिवार के अन्य सदस्यों के साथ तस्वीरें पोस्ट की थीं, लेकिन उन्होंने अपनी पत्नी आरती के साथ कोई तस्वीर शेयर नहीं की थी.
.
.
इस घटना की वजह से वीरेंद्र सहवाग और उनकी पत्नी आरती अहलावत के बीच बढ़ती दूरियों का संकेत मिलता है. दो हफ्ते पहले, वीरेंद्र सहवाग ने केरल के पलक्कड़ में पुलिक्कल विश्व नागयक्षी मंदिर का दौरा किया और अपने इंस्टाग्राम अकाउंट पर इसकी तस्वीरें शेयर कीं. हालांकि इस पोस्ट में आरती का कोई जिक्र नहीं था, जिससे उनके रिश्ते में तनाव का संकेत मिलता है. हालांकि वीरेंद्र सहवाग और उनकी पत्नी आरती अहलावत ने अभी तक कोई आधिकारिक बयान जारी नहीं किया है, लेकिन इस कपल की दूरी से हड़कंप मचा हुआ है. वीरेंद्र सहवाग अपनी वाइफ आरती अहलावत से पहली बार तब मिले जब वह सिर्फ 7 साल के थे. आरती की बुआ की शादी सहवाग के कजिन से हुई थी, इस हिसाब से दोनों परिवार रिश्तों में बंध गए. आरती की बड़ी बहन ने एक इंटरव्यू में बताया था कि वीरेंद्र सहवाग और आरती की शादी फैमिली में हुई. ये लव मैरिज थी. हमारी बुआ (पापा की बहन) की शादी सहवाग की फैमिली में उनके कजिन से हुई थी. इस शादी के बाद वीरेंद्र और हमारी बुआ के बीच देवर-भाभी का रिश्ता हो गया.

Russian oligarch Roman Abramovich dodged millions in tax through pretend superyacht hire schemes, a BBC investigation has found. 
 
Bogus charter records were part of a decade-long scheme to mislead tax authorities. 
 
The billionaire fleet of yachts were falsely presented as a commercial leasing operations, to dodge millions of euros in VAT on their purchase and running costs. 
 
Lawyers representing Mr Abramovich told the BBC he denied knowing of any deception to evade tax and always acted on expert advice.
 
The former Chelsea owner was sanctioned by the UK in March 2022 over his connection with Vladimir Putin’s regime.
 
Over 400,000 files and 72,000 emails have been leaked from a Cypriot corporate service provider, MeritServus, revealing the scheme and other secrets of Abramovich’s corporate empire.
 
Tap the link in @BBCNews’s bio to find out how he dodged millions in tax.
 
📸: Alamy / Getty Images

The man tasked by President Trump to deport unlawful migrants at the Mexico border has defended the government's plan after Selena Gomez's tearful Instagram video.
 
In the clip, she said: All my people are being attacked, and children.
 
"I wish I could do something but I can't," the actress, who has Mexican heritage, added.

Gomez deleted her original video but returned to social to respond to her critics. She later removed that as well.
 
Tom Homan, a veteran immigration official and ex-police officer, responded, saying "we're going to make our community safer".

Google will change the name of the Gulf of Mexico to the Gulf of America in its Google Maps app.
 
The company announced the change after US President Donald Trump ordered that the body of water be renamed in US government documents.
 
Renaming the Gulf appeared to be a high priority for Trump - who mentioned it in his inaugural address just 20 minutes after taking the oath of office on 20 January.
 
The change in name will only appear for Google Maps users in the US.
 
Google also said its US app users would see North America's highest mountain, Mount Denali, revert to its previous name of Mount McKinley, following a separate renaming push from Trump.
 
Mexico's president, Claudia Sheinbaum, poked fun at his renaming decision and even initially sarcastically suggested renaming North America as "América Mexicana".

More often than not, DIY skincare is not safe. We are not against recipes like a quick, simple and effective face mask made from crushed oat and honey, or a body scrub with coffee grounds and olive oil. But homemade beauty that’s more elaborate than this presents a few downsides: a lack of preservatives or ingredients such as lemon juice, baking soda, or cinnamon that are too harsh on the skin and can cause more harm than good. 

If you want to keep your skincare affordable, you can always switch more expensive face and body creams with multipurpose body butters and oils such as jojoba, coconut and shea butter. And if you’re looking for tried and tested DIY beauty recipes, our sister brand @acalaonline offers beautiful sets, from skincare to makeup ranges, to have fun and experiment with creating your own tinted lip balms, or toothpaste, for instance. We are linking Acala’s homepage in our bio! 💚

As a good rule of thumb, you should always check your skincare products’ expiry date and PAO, period after opening. 
All of our products contain natural preservatives which can prolong their shelf life, so they are safe to use even a little after expiration, but you should also keep in mind that all beauty products expire, even if they have not been opened, and those, too, you should discard. 

Expired skincare or makeup can cause redness, breakouts, irritation or just lose the potency of the results they would normally deliver. Check for the open-jar symbol on the back of your products: the number on it indicates its shelf life.

As the winter season is officially upon us, it’s that time of the year where our skin is most in need of extra TLC, hydration, and moisture. So here are some quick and easy tips on how to keep your whole body nourished and radiant. ⛄️ 

1) Follow a skincare routine that is specific to colder weather: apply a thick water-based face and body cream followed by a natural oil of your choice (like jojoba or shea butter) to lock in moisture, and try to adopt a night-time routine, too; 2) Remember to exfoliate: not a summer-only but a year-round good practice, exfoliation helps with skin rejuvenation; 3) Healthy skin starts from the inside out, so try to switch to a more nourishing eating regimen, implementing mineral-rich veggies, seeds for omega, and warming herbal teas for hydration. 4) Keep your skin barrier strong: if you can, avoid extreme cold and indoor heating, both causes of a more dry and irritated skin. 

If you are intrigued to discover more of our skincare experts’ suggestions, read our blog by clicking the link in our bio.

Not to be dramatic, but this gochujang mac & cheese might be the best thing to happen to us all month 🤤🌶️

INGREDIENTS
1 box GOODLES “Vegan Be Heroes”
1 tbsp vegan butter
½ cup vegan milk of choice
1 tbsp gochujang
1-2 tbsp reserved pasta water
Salt & pepper to taste
1 sliced green onion

DIRECTIONS
1. Begin by boiling your box of GOODLES for 8-10 minutes. Be sure to reserve 1-2 tbsp of pasta water for the sauce. Strain and set aside with a drizzle of oil.
2. Next, melt the butter in a pan and add the milk. Add the gochujang and mix well, bringing to a simmer.
3. Shut off the heat and stir in the cheese packets. Stir in the pasta water to create a nice smooth sauce.
4. Add the cooked noodles into the sauce and stir until coated. Serve with sliced green onion and enjoy!

1 box GOODLES Shell We Dance
1/2c white cheddar cheese 
2 Hot Girl Pickles (original dill)
2tbs Hot Girl Pickle Brine (original dill) 

Dill breading: 
3/4c ap flour 
1c breadcrumbs 
 2 eggs, beaten 
1tbs Hot Girl Pickle brine (original dill)
 ½ tsp garlic powder 
½ tsp onion powder 
2tsp dried dill 
Pinch of salt 

1. Make your GOODLES according to package instructions.
2. Add your shredded cheese, chopped pickles, and pickle juice to the cooked mac. Mix well, then place in the fridge for at least 2 hours, or until completely firm.
3. Scoop the mixture into balls and arrange them on a parchment-lined sheet. Place in the freezer while you prepare your breading station.
4. Preheat your air fryer to 400°F for 5 minutes.
5. Set up three separate bowls: one with flour, one with beaten eggs and pickle juice, and one with breadcrumbs and spices. Roll each ball in flour, then coat with the egg mixture, and finally cover with the breadcrumb mixture. Gently press the breadcrumbs to adhere and lightly spray with cooking spray for even browning.
6. Air fry at 380°F for 10–12 minutes, or until golden. Serve warm with your favorite dipping sauce. Enjoy!

Animated painting tutorial. Edited on my Intel AI PC – the DELL XPS 13 powered by Intel Core Ultra.​ Detailed tips below:​

Shortcut sequence:
1. Press Q (this enters quick mask mode)​
2. Set the foreground color to dark grey​
Tip: darker grey will get you closer to the original image, while lighter grey will let Photoshop be more creative with the paint strokes​
3. Press alt-backspace, which applies the color and creates a transparent selection​
4. Press Q again (to exit quick mask mode)​
5. Click “Generative Fill” and type “oil painting”​

How do you get the frames to be consistent with each other?​
It’s a bit of trial and error. Each time you try generative fill you get 3 results, and I go through them to pick out the one that is most consistent with the previous frame. If none of them are consistent, then I try generating again.​

Do you have to go frame by frame?​
With this technique using Photoshop Generative Fill you have to go frame by frame, and using an Intel powered AI PC can speed things up when you’re working with a lot of images. But there are other techniques (e.g. using ComfyUI) that let you apply a painting effect to an entire video. See my May 7 post caption for that workflow. Using ComfyUI lets you get a more consistent look, however sometimes I prefer the stylistic paint brush goopyness of Photoshop’s Generative Fill paint effect.​

Credits​
video by @karenxcheng​
producer @katalinadrojas​
client @intel​

#IntelAmbassador #IntelCoreUltra #AIPC #Dell​

special thanks:​

I learned the shorcut sequence from @piximperfect @unmeshdinda and the video technique from @paolomarktwo​

Thanks to @intel for sponsoring my art! See my process below:

1. Take pictures in different poses
2. Remove background in Photoshop. Intel has partnered with Adobe to optimize AI-related tasks like this one. Especially useful when you’re editing lots of images
3. Bring the images into Adobe Premiere to test out the flow of the choreography
4. The trickiest part was figuring out how the choreography played with gravity, so I iterated and repeated steps 1-3 over and over until it felt right
5. I wanted the video to have a flipbook feel, so I printed the pictures out and captured them in stop motion
6. Final step, add music and sound effects

2024 has been NOW’s 56th anniversary year and we have much to be thankful for. We are so thankful for our employees, suppliers and especially loyal and long-term customers. Thanksgiving is a helpful reminder to all for daily food, health, family, safety and more.  We work hard to put honesty and integrity into every product we sell. It’s part of our DNA and mission – “to empower people to lead healthier lives by providing healthy products, at great values.”
 
My dad, Elwood Richard started NOW in 1968 as a very small brand in five Chicago-area health food stores. He set up NOW to offer great value by avoiding middleman distributors, expensive advertising, and fancy packaging. Though we have come a long way with our packaging and marketing, we remain committed to the original, simple plan to make quality natural products affordable for all. 
 
We appreciate your support and wish you and your family a safe and healthy holiday season.
 
Dan Richard & The Richard Family Ownership

Chocolate protein chia pudding is my current breakfast hyperfixation. 

I finally tried the @c4energy Hershey’s chocolate protein powder flavor and I fear I’m addicted. This will be on repeat until further notice. #c4energy #c4partner

Ingredients
1 1/2 cups unsweetened vanilla almond milk
1/4 cup sugar free maple syrup (or any sweetener of choice)
1/2 cup chia seeds
2 scoops @c4energy Hershey’s chocolate protein powder 
1 tbsp unsweetened cocoa powder
Toppings: yogurt and raspberries

Instructions:
1. Add all ingredients to a high speed blender, blend until it starts to thicken into a pudding like texture. This may take some time!
2 Evenly distribute amongst 3 glass jars then top with yogurt and raspberries, store in the fridge for up to 4 days.

Making MOEDER has been a journey - and those who have shared in the journey with me can probably attest to the emotional ups and downs, but tonight and this week is special (albeit somewhat nerve-wracking): MOEDER/MOTHER is screening at @clermontisff in front of some sizey audiences (eeeek!!!) 

It plays TONIGHT at 19:30 at the 900 seat ‘L’HORIZON’ theatre and at the 1400 seat ‘COCTEAU’ theatre on MONDAY at 21:30. 

More screening times to follow!

What an immense privilege to have the work be shown here…although I hope I don’t get a heart-attack. 

Thankful for the endless amount of people who went on the journey with me. @farhadghaderi_ @linnikzhuravliov @dbskills @neokerz @human_giant @mikeypackage @blacksmithvfx @borotalco.tv @radioaktivefilm @joeperri @noahagemo @juhoviktor @chriszahariev @chris_galust #lucadegani @martabiloshapka @heyitsalexfarah @cstropko #lukeatencio to name a few!

‘THE HOUSE OF DILIGENCE’ is a film close to the heart. It’s been a blessing being able to document the work of Father Vadim at @givinghopenyc over the past year or so. His 20+ year long work on the streets of Brighton Beach and Coney Island - despite the mafia, governmental red-tape, and harsh winters trying to shut him down, still fervently continues. His house contains a small church inside and a couple of bedrooms that house people battling addiction. The arc of these stories sometimes take a while to reveal its shape, but it’s such a great privilege to be there, and to see a man walk so definitively in his mission.
